title: creole chicken
directions: Broil chicken until lightly browned.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add onion and saute about 3 minutes.
Add onion and garlic and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, pepper and salt and cook, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes.

title: han's red cabbage
directions: Step 1:
Remove outer leaves and cut cabbage into quarters; discard core.
Shred.
Should measure 10 cups.

title: dad's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Layer in large pan or casserole dish, bananas, wafers and pudding mixed with canned Eagle Brand milk.
Top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator. Extra good.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Chill overnight.

title: frozen date salad
directions: Make up Dream Whip as package directs.
Cream the cheese and pineapple.
Add dates and nuts.
Fold maple syrup into Dream Whip. Combine the two mixtures.
Put into 8 x 8-inch pan and freeze until firm.
Serves 8.

title: mashed turnips and butter
directions: Cover sliced turnips
with water and boil until tender. Remove from water and mash, adding the salt, pepper, sugar and the butter.
In
the
empty
pot, replace the turnips and heat for 5 to
10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
Peel and slice about 1/2 ick thick. Combine syrup, sugar and butter.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook until syrup is thick.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Mix together 1 1/4 cups brown sugar, oil, vanilla, egg whites and buttermilk.
Stir in the flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Fold in the rhubarb. Mix together the cinnamon, butter and 1/3 cup brown sugar. Scatter over the muffins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 20 muffins.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with crackers or bagels.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion salt and celery salt; mix well.
Place cereals and nuts in heavy roaster.
Mix well with butter mixture.
Place in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: candy glazed carrots
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma fry's apple pie
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt honey and chocolate over a low flame.
Beat egg whites fast.
Add cream of tartar and beat until egg whites are stiff. Quickly fold in chocolate mixture.
Pour into dessert dishes and refrigerate for 3 - 4 hours.
Makes 3 servings.

title: potato tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half (across, not up and down).
Scoop out pulp, leaving enough veins to make 3 pockets.
Discard pulp (or save for salsa).
Be sure to cut out the large core on one half of each tomato.
Place them open side up on cookie sheet.
Salt and pepper if desired.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese. Precook in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine and blend well the butter, sugar, flour and salt; add eggs, then corn syrup and milk.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 50 minutes.

title: summertime salad
directions: In mixing bowl, pour dry jello over cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix into punch bowl and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 11 x 14-inch pan.
Put half the bread cubes in bottom. Add half the cheese, then sausage, mixed with crumbled bacon.
Add remaining bread and cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown and done.
May be prepared ahead of time and frozen.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, milk, dry ingredients and vanilla.
Blend together.
Roll on floured surface to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes just until skins can be removed easily.
Cut into serving pieces and place in rectangular baking dish.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, oleo and crushed pineapple.
Heat until blended.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: zachery's mexican casserole
directions: Place ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with corn chips. "Hot peppers can also be added."
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flours together and add to creamed mixture. Fold in strawberries and juice. Add nuts. Spoon batter into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour.

title: chinese barbecue pork
directions: Blend marinade sauce together.
Place the pork tenderloins in the marinade and let set at least 3 hours or overnight.
Line cooking sheet with foil and place a cooking rack on the foil. Roast at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn and roast for 25 more minutes. Let set for 10 minutes and then slice in thin slices.
Serve with hot mustard, sweet sauce and sesame seed.
This is a great appetizer and can be made the day ahead and then just reheated.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Add white sugar. Mix well till sugar is dissolved. Add Cool Whip. Stir till well blended. Place in graham cracker crust. Top with cherry pie filling. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Whisk together egg and mayonnaise.
Blend in mushroom soup. Pour over broccoli, which has been cooked and drained.
Stir in onion and Swiss cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top before baking.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks. Add pineapple and coconut. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, Karo, butter and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange walnuts on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°; bake 35 or 45 minutes, or until center appears set. Cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cans of soup.
Mix all ingredients.
Add water.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic shrimp with red peppers and wild mushrooms
directions: Char peppers over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides. Transfer to paper bag and let stand 10 minutes to steam.
Peel, seed and quarter peppers.
Arrange peppers on platter.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Drain broccoli, combine all ingredients in order listed, mixing well pour in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 2 to 4 minutes.
Take off heat, add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Whip good with spoon.
Add walnuts.
Put in greased 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage
set
until real soft.
Mix all ingredients and form into small
balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 400°.
May	be
fixed
ahead
of time and frozen until ready to bake.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Stir together confectioners sugar, cocoa and salt in 2-quart glass dish.
Stir in milk and vanilla extract until well blended. Melt margarine in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on Medium-high. Stir margarine into mixture.
Microwave mixture for 2 minutes on High.
Add nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into clean dish, if desired, for serving.
Chill until set.

title: recipe for living
directions: Light oven; get out utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toy autos from table; grease pan.
Crack nuts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together and place in 2-quart casserole, greased.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well with fork. Put into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: roasted potatoes with caramelized garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and heat in oven for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, tossing to coat them.
Roast, turning occasionally, 30 to 35 minutes, or until tender.

title: chinese cheese wafers
directions: Dredge cheese with flour.
Cream oleo and seasonings.
Mix in cheese mixture and blend thoroughly.
Roll out and cut into small wafers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light brown. These may be dropped.

title: oriental barbecue sauce
directions: In a small bowl, stir ingredients.
Brush on chicken, pork chops, spareribs or steak during the last 20 minutes of grilling.

title: turkey crescent pie
directions: Melt margarine; add flour.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add half and half; stir well.
Continue heating on low heat.
Add turkey, asparagus, mushrooms and cheese.
Line pie pan with crescent rolls in a star pattern.
Flatten to form crust.
Pour in turkey mixture.
Bring points of dough over top of pie.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: shrimp
directions: Lay shrimp on cookie sheet.
Crush Ritz crackers and cover shrimp.
Melt butter and combine with garlic powder.
Cook 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with drawn butter.

title: dill pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water and sugar together.
Cut up cucumbers and put in jars.
Put 1 teaspoon dill seed in each jar and fill with vinegar mixture.
Seal and let set for at least four weeks before opening.
Yields 10 pints.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: tasty low-fat fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes. Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly until it melts. Pour over cooked pasta and toss to coat well.
Top with remaining cheese, parsley and pepper.
Yields 4 cups.
Contains 345 calories, 9.7 grams fat per serving.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a large bowl. Combine buttermilk, egg and butter. Add to flour mixture and stir just until all ingredients are moistened. Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups about 2/3 full. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm with butter or preserves. Makes 1 dozen.

title: pineapple cream jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and juice from pineapple. Add cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup and let jello start to jell, then add pineapple and softened cream cheese.
If you have chopped pecans, you can add them to jello (optional). Let stand in icebox until all is set.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Into large bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt (if desired).
Stir in cornmeal and mix well.
In medium size bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Stir in milk and oil until blended. Pour this over cornmeal mixture; stir only until moistened (do not overmix).

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream softened butter
or
oleo
and
sugar; add flour, salt and vanilla Stir in egg yolks and gradually stir in milk. Cook on medium heat
until	thick
and then add coconut.
Pour into baked 9-inch
pie shell.	While preparing meringue, place pie in 325° oven.
(This
will	prevent moisture from forming between filling and meringue when pie is finished.)

title: yogurt crunch
directions: With Dad or Mom helping, place yogurt in a medium bowl.
Add granola with raisins and chopped bananas.
Fold lightly to blend. Share with your family and friends!
Choose any seasonal fruits in place of bananas.

title: fudge pie
directions: With electric mixer mix all ingredients
and
pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40
minutes
or until knife inserted
into
middle
comes out
slightly
"fudgy"
looking. Cool, serve plain or with scoop of vanilla ice cream on top.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
Spread the pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix as package directs.
Spread on coconut and pecans.
Mix the butter, melted with the powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread evenly on cake batter.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325° (cake will not cook done).
Put in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli as package directs.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, eggs and onion with broccoli. Pour in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix butter, water and stuffing mix, spread over broccoli.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked celery 'n mushrooms
directions: Place celery and mushrooms on large foil squares.
Sprinkle with onion, salt
and pepper. Drizzle with butter.
Close foil tightly. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice rolls.
Mix mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, margarine and onion.
Spread on rolls.
Place cheese and ham in roll.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients thoroughly with mayonnaise.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spice teacher's tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into airtight jars.
Use 2 teaspoons for each cup of hot water.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Wash and cap berries.
Cover with 1 cup sugar.
Allow to sit for about 30 minutes.
Mix lemon juice with berries.
Combine flour with 4 tablespoons sugar, ground cinnamon, salt and ground cloves.
Gently stir into the berry-sugar mixture.
Spoon into prepared pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top pastry.
Cut several gashes in top crust.
Bake at 405° about 40 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a beater.
Pour over steaks. Let marinate overnight.
Broil to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute vegetables; add soups and chopped up chicken in large bowl.
Grease a large casserole dish and put a layer of crushed chips and a layer of chicken mixture and cheese.
Top with cheese last.
Bake at 425° until done, but don't overcook, it will be too dry.

title: carrot pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix well, then stir in carrots and pineapple.
Spray pans with Pam.
Fill bread pans 3/4 and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Breads will be very moist when done.

title: baked ziti with broccoli
directions: Cook ziti using package directions for 10 minutes.
Drain. Saute garlic in olive oil in skillet for 1 minute.
Drain thawed broccoli.
Combine ziti, garlic, broccoli, Parmesan cheese and cream in bowl; mix lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: crazy quick candy
directions: Place corn syrup in a small 1-quart saucepan.
Boil until syrup turns golden brown.
Pour hot corn syrup over peanut butter, beating on medium speed of mixer.
Mix until ingredients are combined.
Immediately turn out on a buttered cookie sheet and pat out to about 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, spread one side with melted sweet chocolate.
Let chocolate harden, then turn candy over and spread other side with chocolate.
Break or cut into pieces. Makes about 40 pieces.

title: christmas jam
directions: Mix up gud...fur ever 5 cups uv the mixture, add 3 cups uv sugah 'n cook only fur a few minutes.
Cut 3 slices each uv red 'n green crystalized pineapple fur each jar to make it look Christmussy...jar 'n seal.

title: egg dish for breakfast or brunch
directions: Wisk eggs and combine other ingredients.
Make sure ham, bacon or mushrooms have been cooked.
Pour into 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: green chili chicken soup
directions: Cook
chicken,	onions,
garlic
and
half of sherry in chicken broth for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut chilies in chunks and tear tomatoes apart
with
2 forks.
Take chicken out and add tomatoes, chilies and rest of sherry.
Add salt, pepper, basil and Mexican seasoning
to
taste
and
simmer
for
1 hour.
Cube chicken and put back in before serving to get hot.
Put grated Monterey Jack cheese in bottom of bowl and put soup on top and serve.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove shells from crabmeat.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk to make white sauce.
Add seasoning, eggs and crabmeat.
Put in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: simple potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onion.
Put potatoes, onion and salt in pan and cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender, adding a little water if necessary.

Empty can of soup into pan and add milk gradually (may not need all of it at this point). Stir ingredients together and continue cooking over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is heated thoroughly.
If soup appears too thick, add a small amount of milk until desired consistency is reached.

title: blueberry 'n spice sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Gradually stir in water and ReaLemon.
Over medium heat, cook constantly until thick and comes to boil.
Add blueberries. Cook and stir until mixture comes to boil.
Serve over ice cream.

title: lo-cal pizza casserole
directions: Brown turkey; drain.
Add veggies and V-8.
Put in glass dish. Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cool before icing.

title: ritz cookie bars
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add vanilla. Roll crackers to fine crumbs; add all dry ingredients to crackers.
Mix and fold into egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9 or 10-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook; cut into squares.

title: alma's microwave double chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
Stir milk and chips in 2-quart casserole.
Add chocolate.
Microwave on High 1 minute and stir. Microwave about 2 more minutes until chips and chocolate are melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly in pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: quick veg-all casserole
directions: Melt margarine and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until blended well. Drain Veg-All and add to margarine and cheese mixture.
Put into well-greased casserole dish.
Add crushed Ritz crackers to top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown the hamburger in a 2-quart or bigger cooking pot. Halfway through the browning process, add the diced onion, salt and pepper to taste and 1 to 2 tablespoons of chili powder.
Drain if needed.
Add the cans of kidney beans, juice and all.
Add tomato juice.
Cook on medium heat until it starts to boil.
Stir often.
Turn down to low heat and simmer for at least 1 hour.
You can add more chili powder if you like it hotter.
This is always better the next day.

title: apple pie extra
directions: *Flour 1 side of bottom crust and place in pie pan, flour side down.

title: fried rice
directions: Use oil to moisten rice and soy sauce to taste.
Place all ingredients in a large frypan.
Cook until crisp.

title: pasta fagiole
directions: Place olive oil in a saucepan.
Brown the chopped onion in the oil.
Cut the potato into small pieces.
Brown the potato.
Add the beans, water and catsup.
Let the mixture simmer until the potato is tender.
Add the macaroni; cook until tender, 7 to 8 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except whipping cream. Beat on high speed for 20 minutes until stiff. Fold in whipping cream. Pile high into baked and chilled 10-inch pie crust. Place in freezer overnight until served.

title: two, two and two cake
directions: In bowl, mix the two, two, two together, then if you want fruit, put that at the bottom of the greased pan. If not, pour the batter into pan and bake for 1 hour or a little more until nice and brown.

title: california roll-ups
directions: Mix everything.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up tight.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, insert toothpicks to secure, and slice between them into bite-size pieces.
Serve with picante sauce or salsa.

title: cowboy bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and beans until smooth.
In a separate bowl, put the next 4 ingredients.
Add to bean mixture just until combined. Stir in raisins and vanilla. Fill two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lucky chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in
oil.
Mix butter, red and green peppers, celery, ketchup, brown sugar and onions.
Pour over browned chicken.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: christine's egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Wrap in lumpia wrappers. Heat oil in skillet.
Fry egg rolls until golden brown.
Dip in sweet and sour sauce.

title: white cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, shortening and 2/3 cup milk.
Blend at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add the remaining milk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend at medium for 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place cheese and onion on each breast and fold chicken over cheese and onion. Secure with toothpicks.
Dip into eggs and crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over to cover chicken and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lentils and rice
directions: In medium size saucepan, saute onion in olive oil over medium heat.
Add 2 cups water and lentils; boil until lentils are tender.
Add rice and enough water to cook rice until done.
Serve as side dish or main dish.

title: more
directions: Brown meat, sausage, onion and garlic.
Add corn, peas, mushrooms and olive after drained and cut up.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook the macaroni.
Drain, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna seashell casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine over medium heat.
Add celery and onion.
Cook, stirring, 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over macaroni mixture.
Mix bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly, at 350°. Serves 6.

title: lazy day cake
directions: Beat until thick the eggs.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Heat to boiling point the milk and shortening.
Add all at once to the mixture, beating well.
(Do not add any more flour as this batter is very thin.) Pour in 8-inch cake pan and bake 30 minutes in moderate oven (350° to 375°).

title: holiday wreaths
directions: In large pan, melt butter over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper, then add red cinnamon candies.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream 1/2 cup shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then chocolate, melted.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar and flour in casserole dish.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Pour in 1/3 of the pineapple juice and stir well.
In separate bowl, combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy potato salad dressing
directions: Mix and combine with cooked potatoes, chopped onions, chopped celery and chopped green peppers.
Season with onion salt and celery salt to taste.

title: venerable vegetable bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent roll dough into 2 strips; pinch together into rectangular shape in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for about 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Mix Ranch dressing, softened cream cheese and milk; spread onto cooled dough.
Sprinkle vegies on, then cheese last.
Chill for 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.

title: oriental burgers
directions: Combine meat, pepper, water and garlic.
Shape into 6 patties. Brown hamburgers in heated oil in frying pan, 3 minutes each side.
Combine ginger, soy sauce, water chestnuts and honey.
Pour ginger mixture over hamburgers in pan and cook over low heat for about 5 minutes, turning often.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with 1 less cup milk than total box directions call for.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Add Cool Whip to pudding.
Add 1/2 pudding mixture, another layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding mixture, another layer of graham crackers.

title: broccoli rice with cheese
directions: Cook broccoli to package directions.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute onion in melted oleo until the onion is clear.
Add chopped broccoli.
Add mushroom soup and stir; simmer a few minutes.
Add cheese and 1/2 cup of water.
Mix and simmer a few minutes.
Add 2 cups of cooked rice.
Bake, uncovered, in casserole dish for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
This can be made ahead of time and stored in refrigerator.

title: pasta with camembert and tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, Camembert, basil, garlic, 1/2 cup olive oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper in a serving bowl.
Prepare at least 2 to 3 hours before serving and set aside, covered, at room temperature.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Prepare eggs, peppers and celery. Mix all ingredients.
May add extra mayonnaise.
May serve cold.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add uncooked rice, soup and cheese. Leave some cheese for top.	Cook at 350° for around 20 or more minutes or until top is bubbly.

title: sand tarts
directions: Make a double recipe.
Cream butter and sugar and then add egg.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
When all mixed, take a large handful out of bowl.
Press together into a long roll, about 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator until well chilled and firm.

title: cafe mocha
directions: Mix well.
Add 2 - 3 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water or milk.
Good to use as a gift.

title: crackers for hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix oil and powdered salad mix, bring to a boil.
Pour over crackers. Put onto cookie sheet in 200 degree oven for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Put into air tight container and refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook pecans and onion in butter until tender.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Combine dry ingredients and mix in with sugar mixture. Add sour cream; mix well. Add vanilla and coconut; mix well.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Add eggs and food coloring.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips over low heat.
Pour cereal in a large shallow pan (broiler pan works well).
Drizzle chocolate mixture over cereal while tossing evenly to coat.
Pour 1 box of confectioners sugar in a large bag.
Add cereal and toss to coat.

title: mama's old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add molasses.
Stir.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, stirring after each addition. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: danish puff pastry
directions: Boil water with butter until butter is melted.
Add flour all at once and stir until it forms a ball.
Add flavoring, then add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Set aside.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and softened butter; mix well.
Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until creamy.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Spread your favorite topping and enjoy.
Triple recipe for 2 pies.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds casserole pan.

title: caramel-nut pinwheels
directions: In a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan, stir together topping and melted margarine.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Separate, but do not uncoil, breadsticks.
Arrange dough coils in pan and top with nuts.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Loosen sides and invert onto serving plate.
Spread any remaining topping on rolls.
Serve warm.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Blend to a puree.
Transfer to bowl and fold in whipped cream. Chill up to 4 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle crumbled cheese crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dilly macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Cool.
Combine macaroni, cheese, celery and green pepper.
Blend together the mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and dill weed; add to macaroni mixture.
Toss lightly.
Cover and chill well.
Serve salad in lettuce lined bowl, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: key west chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a shallow, medium dish, blend soy sauce, honey, vegetable oil, lime juice and garlic. Place chicken into the mixture. Marinate in the refrigerator at least 30 minutes. Marinate overnight for fullest flavor. Place dish in oven and bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until chicken is cooked through and juices run clear.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add marshmallows and let melt.
Add pineapple juice. Mix and chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts, then fold in whipped cream.
Pour into favorite mold and refrigerate.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Shape into crescents and bake 250° for 1 hour or 300° for 25 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm. Chill the dough 1 hour before baking for ease of handling.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and add milk if necessary.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions (10 minutes for fresh broccoli).
Add 1/3 stick butter (softened) and cheese. Crush crackers and melt the remaining butter and combine both butter and crushed crackers.
In a greased casserole dish, put broccoli and top with cracker mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot and enjoy!

title: baldhead island chicken nuggets
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
Wash chicken breasts and cut each one in half lengthwise.
Dip in melted margarine, followed by bread crumb mixture.
Lay flat on a baking pan (I use a jelly roll sheet).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with linguine, potato casserole or seasoned rice.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In large pan, brown ground chuck with onion, minced garlic and chili powder.
Drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients except sharp cheese and Tostitos.
Stir until ingredients are mixed well. In large baking dish layer Tostitos and meat mixture.
Sprinkle sharp cheese on top.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 10 minutes.
Serve with remaining Tostitos chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into ball.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Beat half and half and pie filling mix in large mixing bowl with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in topping and remaining ingredients; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes to soften.
Store in freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil breasts in broth until done.
Steam broccoli and carrots in microwave for 5 minutes.
Then add all ingredients together (except rolls) in casserole dish.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Place crescent rolls on top of casserole, then cook at 350° until rolls are brown.
Serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter with 1/2 cup of the Cool Whip.
Mix pudding with the milk in another bowl.
Now add the peanut butter mixture and all the remaining Cool Whip using hand mixer.
Put into pie shell and chill for 2 hours.
You may top with more Cool Whip if desired.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Soak break in milk.
Combine meat, onions, bread, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Cook in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fish flair
directions: Marinate fish in salad dressing for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Broil, bottom side up, until slightly brown, 5 or 6 minutes.
Combine crumbs and cheese.
Put on fish, right side up.
Broil for about 7 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add one can of sweetened condensed milk and cook over very low heat, stirring constantly.
May store in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: chocolate ice cream dessert
directions: Mix chocolate, sugar, evaporated milk and 1 tablespoon oleo together.
Cook until slightly thick.
Cook ahead.
Butter 2 x 13-inch pan well.
Mix cookie crumbs and melted oleo and press in pan.
Refrigerate for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream on top of cookie mix.
Pour chocolate mix over ice cream.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep in freezer.

title: cranberry cocktail punch
directions: Just before serving:
In large punch bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients. Makes 15 cups.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten egg.
Add flour, soda and salt that have been sifted together.
Add nuts and vanilla. Mix well.
Shape into a long roll.
Place in refrigerator and let stand until hard.
Slice thin and bake in a 350° oven.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add teaspoons to taste to hot water.

title: miss nettie g. brinkley's whipped pet milk lemon pie
directions: Dissolve
the jello with the boiling water.
Add sugar, cream cheese
and
lemon.
Cool.	Chill the canned milk, have bowl and beaters
cold.
Then
whip until stiff.
Fold in the jello mixture and pour into a baked crust or a graham cracker crust.
Makes 3 pies.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Prepare Bisquick mix according to package directions for biscuit dough, using required liquid.
Roll dough on a lightly floured surface to a rectangle, 15 x 18-inches and about 1/8-inch thick.
Dot entire surface with pieces of fresh sausage.
Sprinkle with chives.
Cut dough in half crosswise.
Roll each half jelly roll fashion toward the center, making 2 rolls.
Chill for easy slicing (or freeze).

title: cranberry candied yams
directions: Make crumb mixture with first five ingredients.
Mix 1 cup mixture with yams, cranberries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Place in baking dish and top with remainder of crumb mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; top with marshmallows and brown.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: *Half whole wheat and unbleached white flours.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, pecans, 1 egg and butter. Spread mixture in bottom of lightly greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients until smooth and pour over cake layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: susan's broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Melt cheese in milk over low heat; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over casserole and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nebraska corn pie
directions: Place 3 strips of slightly cooked bacon in the bottom of a baking dish.
Place the other strips around the sides.
Add a layer of bread crumbs and then a layer of peeled, sliced tomatoes and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Over this, place a layer of corn and continue with alternate layers until the dish is filled.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: marvelous muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg until frothy; stir in milk and butter.
Make "well" in center of flour mixture.
Pour all of milk mixture.
Stir quickly until just mixed but still lumpy.
Fill large muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients
in a large mixing bowl, in order listed.
Mix at high speed for two minutes.
Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake about 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: irishmen's delight
directions: Sprinkle wafers and crackers (crushed with rolling pin) on oiled paper in large cake pan, leaving not quite half of mixture for the top.
Spread beaten eggs on top as smoothly as possible. Add melted butter; spread evenly.
Spread cooled pineapple on top. Spread with whipped cream sweetened with a little sugar. Sprinkle the remaining crumb mixture on top.
Press down firmly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion.
Drain and mix with mixed vegetables. Stir in cheese until melted.
Add mayonnaise.
Pour in dish and top with crushed crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven until crackers are golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick and clear.
Take off stove and stir in 1 box strawberry jello.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before pouring over strawberries in a cooked 9-inch pie crust.

title: chicken kun koki
directions: Combine onion flakes, soy sauce, pepper and water.
Bring to boil.
Put in chicken pieces and cook (simmer) until chicken is done.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: *Grate all lemon rind in a small bowl and squeeze all lemon juice in with grated rind (approximately 1/4 cup).

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin pie mix, eggs and milk in large bowl (add sugar if desired).
Pour into ungreased baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over top. Sprinkle chopped pecans over the top.
Bake at 350° for one hour to one hour and twenty minutes.
Insert knife in the center.
If clean, it's done.
Best served warm with whipped topping.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well and chill at least 2 hours.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Pour soda on chopped dates and pour boiling water over soda and dates; let cool about 20 minutes.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix water mixture of dates and flour, 1/3 at a time. Add sugar mixture and add nuts.
Bake in angel food pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with cherries (optional).

title: chicken with beer
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Skin chicken and dredge with flour mixture.
Fry in oil until brown.
Mix soup, soy sauce, beer, 2 tablespoons almonds and mushrooms.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour the soup mixture over it.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, basting several times.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle remaining almonds over the top and serve warm.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apples into greased baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until apples are done.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Drain off fat.
Add sausage, garlic and parsley and cook until sausage is done.
Stir in tomatoes and bacon, mix with spaghetti.
Quickly scramble eggs, add eggs and remaining ingredients to spaghetti; toss lightly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain meat and add remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Mix well.
Line large casserole with tortillas, cover with grated cheese and layer of meat mixture; repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good to make ahead of time and refrigerate until needed.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Store immediately in Ziploc bag.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix cheese, bread and flour.
Add cooked and drained sausage. Put into a large casserole dish.
Beat eggs well.
Add condiments.
Pour mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set in the middle.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 13.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Chop, cook, drain and cool spinach.
Combine 3 beaten eggs, 1/2 stick of softened oleo, 1 pound small curd cottage cheese, 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese and 1/4 teaspoon salt and add cooled spinach.
Add 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix well; pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Add and mix hamburger meat, salt, onion, lemon juice, sugar rice.
Roll in cabbage leaves. Put on top of mixture after cabbage is rolled the whole tomatoes, sugar and lemon juice.
If liquid is low, add water. Cook slowly for 4 hours.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers; set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Place cucumbers in a container and pour mixture over cucumbers.
Seal the container.
Place in refrigerator.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Use 1/3 cup each day.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough and place it in a pizza pan. Bake as directed on package. Cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Place on top of cool cookie crust. Top with various fruits of your chose. Cut and serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together and spread in pie shells. Top with Cool Whip (optional).
Keep refrigerated.

title: mother's sour cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts, butter, egg and cherries.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan that has been buttered.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool.
Serve in squares, topped with whipped cream and a spoonful of Sauce.

title: sweet and sour cheese
directions: Combine jelly, preserves and horseradish.
Pour over cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and Minute rice as the packages suggest.
Drain broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish, adding cream of chicken soup, Minute rice and sharp cheese.
Add some of the dried onion.
Cook at 350° for one hour.
Fifteen minutes before done, remove from oven and add dry onions to top; finish cooking for the last fifteen minutes.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple and mix in, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat eggs, water and oil.
Add cake mix, morsels and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top will be pale yellow.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well with hands.
Shape into a loaf and place in an ovenproof baking dish or pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Remove grease.
Add sauce (recipe follows).
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Toss together with 3 tablespoons mayonnaise blended with 1/2 cup chili sauce.
Mix well and spread in 12 hot dog buns.
Wrap each in foil, twisting ends securely.
Can be made ahead and put in refrigerator.
Bake 10 minutes on cookie sheet at 400°.
These are great with just the ham, cheese and mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix egg, oil and pumpkin.
Stir and add salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, sugar and flour.
Add milk to thin it (about 1 cup).
Stir and cook.

title: clam chowder
directions: Place
all
ingredients in a saucepan.	Cover with just enough water
to	cover
them.
Cook until potatoes are done. Season with salt and pepper.
Add milk and heat slowly.

title: mushroom chicken a la kathy
directions: Dip each cutlet into beaten eggs, then into bread crumbs. Brown cutlets lightly in oil.
In pan, melt the butter; add the garlic, onions and parsley flakes.
Drain the cans of mushrooms and reserve the juice.
Add mushrooms to the pan.
Take the mushroom juice and place in a 1-cup measuring cup.
Now, add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add this to the pan.
Add wine.
Mix altogether in frypan over low heat.
Remove from heat. Arrange chicken in a baking pan, preferably without overlapping. Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: linger cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar and dry ingredients gradually with sour cream. Add vanilla.
Pat all but 2 cups dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Roll out remaining 2 cups dough for strips on top.
Take 2 cans cherry pie filling and spread on top of dough.
Add the strips.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes. Serves 15 or more.

title: spinach dip or spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let ripen overnight in refrigerator. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: crab balls
directions: Chill thoroughly 2 hours.
Roll in little balls and broil on toothpick.

title: jo's punch
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water and stir until dissolved. Add orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice. Mix well. Freeze in 4-quart size containers. Add 1 1/2 quarts ginger ale to each punch mixture. Serves 40 to 50.

title: chinese peanut butter candy
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle some stuffing mix on bottom of Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle with water.
Arrange breasts on top of mix; place piece of cheese on each breast.
Stir together soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with butter and spread over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies(minus the raisins?)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Slowly add flour until you get a somewhat stiff batter.
(You don't want it too stiff as you stil have to add oatmeal).
Add the oatmeal until you get a nice stiff batter. Last of all, add the raisins, unless you have silly children who don't like them in their Oatmeal Raisin Cookies, as I do.

title: dijon sauce for steaks and chicken
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add mushrooms and saute until tender.
Add cooking wine and mustard and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour over cooked steaks or chicken just prior to serving.
Serves 2.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Place turkey in bowl.
Chop garlic, then onion in food processor and add to turkey.
Add nuts, cheese, salt and egg whites.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Put oil in large skillet. Heat oil for 2 to 3 minutes, then cook meatballs.
Serve with yogurt as sauce or may bake meatballs in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: raw zucchini cake
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil.
Cool.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello; allow to congeal.
Mix the cream cheese which has been mixed with pineapple and nuts.
Fold into jello, then fold in the whipping cream.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Place onion, pepper and ground beef in a large skillet and cook, crumbling the beef as it cooks.
After the meat is thoroughly cooked, add the tomato soup using a small amount of water to clean out the soup left in the can.
Stir to mix thoroughly and simmer on low heat 5-10 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add milk slowly, stirring to make mixture smooth.
Add salt and cook until thickened.
Pour some of hot mixture into egg yolks, stirring well.
Pour all together and cook 3 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Add meringue and bake until brown.

title: dressing for tossed salad
directions: Mix together.
Pour into container.
This makes enough for several salads.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine macaroni and next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish. Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Have pan or skillet ready with about 3 tablespoons oil.
Pour mixture in.
Bake at 400° 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add bananas, egg, soda and salt. Add flour.
Beat, add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: peter paul cake
directions: Split layers of cake and make into four separate layers.
Mix sugar, cream and marshmallows.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Simmer five minutes over low heat.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Put between layers of cake.
Ice top with one can dark milk chocolate frosting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 100.

title: feather dumplings
directions: Mix all together, using enough milk to make stiff dough.
Drop batter by spoonfuls, dipping in soup.
Let cook slowly 15 minutes uncovered, then 15 minutes covered.

title: beef stock
directions: In large kettle, combine beef, bay leaves, onion with cloves, celery stalk, carrot, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to boil. Reduce to a simmer.
Skim off froth.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, skimming occasionally.
Strain stock through a sieve and chill, reserving meat.
Discard vegetables.
Shred meat and reserve in refrigerator, covered.
Stock can be refrigerated for 2 to 3 days or frozen for up to 3 months.
Before use, remove congealed fat from top.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Put aside to cool.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, then add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix flour, milk and chocolate mixture together adding a little of each at a time. Fold in egg whites.
Put in greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: meatless greek stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and dry peppers.
Cut caps off peppers and reserve. Remove seeds from peppers.
Mix all ingredients together except peppers.
Reserve some tomatoes for over peppers and liquid for pot.
Stuff each pepper with rice mixture.
Cover with caps. Puncture each pepper.
Place in Dutch oven.
Pour reserved tomatoes over peppers and liquid in pot.
Cover; cook at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
If extra stuffing, place in bread pan.
Cover and cook approximately 1/2 hour.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir well.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Fold in walnuts. Spread in pan and bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Center will be soft.
Cool and serve.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lou's delicious roast
directions: Mix soup and water; pour over roast in a baking dish with lid. Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Makes its own gravy.
Delicious and easy.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a pot, saut the onion in cooking oil.
When the onion is ready, add hot water, enough to cover the 4 chicken breasts with a couple of inches above the chicken breasts.
Season chicken before adding to pot.
When the chicken is tender (I wait until it starts to cook off the bone), remove from the pot.
Remove skin and cut or tear chicken off the bone (small pieces).
Add a can of chicken stock to the water.
Put in your flat noodles.
When the noodles are almost done, you add cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup
and cream of celery soup.
When the soups are dissolved, you can adjust the thickness by adding either water or more chicken stock.
Add a little seasoning to the cut up chicken and then add back to the soup.
You can add parsley flakes at this time if you like.
This is really easy and tastes great!

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° until tender.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Slowly blend in flour with a wire whisk until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add milk, whisking constantly.
Add salt and pepper to taste and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cut baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out potatoes and set aside.
Chop half of the potato skins and discard the rest. When milk mixture is very hot, whisk in potatoes.
Stir in green onions and potato peels, then add sour cream and crumbled bacon. Heat thoroughly.
Gradually add cheese, stirring until all is melted.
Garnish with chives, cheese and bacon crumbles.
Serves 8.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate and peanut butter chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: dixie style pudding cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Mix in flour and pecans with fork and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour.
Combine margarine, cocoa and water in a pan.
Cook to boiling.
Pour over sugar and flour mix.
Mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan (11 x 17-inches).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: yams
directions: Peel yams; cut into large chunks.
Place in saucepan; add fruit juice.
Cook about 20 minutes or until tender.
Mash yams well. Add butter, egg, salt, cinnamon, brown sugar and cream or juice, if needed.
Spoon into well-greased baking dish.

title: coconut mist cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder, salt and sift together three times.
Cream butter thoroughly, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites quickly and thoroughly.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate oven, 375°, for 25 to 30 minutes, or use 2 oblong cake pans.
Spread lemon filling between layers and Seven Minute frosting over the cake.

title: sweet and tangy chicken
directions: Place
chicken	in baking pan.	Mix dressing, sauce and dry soup.
Pour
over chicken.	Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat until smooth (1 minute).
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or in cookie sheet for thinner bread.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick and easy cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Italian dressing.
Add to cauliflower mixture.

title: chicken and dumplings(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place chicken in large Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender (about 2 1/2 hours.)

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mix Jell-O with pineapple.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Add nuts; let chill.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add all ingredients, except sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over mix. Cover with remaining mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: barkies
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a boil; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, Rice Krispies and dates.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Cool on wax paper.
Dip in almond bark.
Good either plain or dipped.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Bring meat, salt, pepper and water to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer while cutting onions, potatoes and celery and adding to broth.
Remove meat to another pan with broth to cover meat and add more water, salt and pepper.
Continue to simmer until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together and pour the following liquid onto the beans:

title: lemon cheese torte
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until fluffy.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat the milk and pudding and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put ingredients in a blender.
Blend well.
Pour mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes. A crust will form on the bottom, pie filling in the center and coconut topping above.

title: sarah hart's best cookies
directions: Mix margarine, oil, sugar and powdered sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and soda together; add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix all together until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until tests done.
Very moist
cake.
Frost as desired or use whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Real good.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla wafers, which have been crushed, alternating with milk.
Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Then pour into a greased and floured 11 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter, shortening and sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and eggs; set mixture aside.
In another large bowl, combine flour (no need to sift), salt, baking soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon. Blend thoroughly with wire whisk.
Gradually mix flour mixture into creamed ingredients until dough is blended and smooth.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar; place 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container to maintain softness.
Yields about 3 dozen cookies.

title: roasted red peppers
directions: Roast at 325° on baking sheet for 45 minutes (approximately), turning until all sides are shriveled (not black!)
Break peppers, allowing juice to run in bowl.
Skin and slice peppers.
Add to juice in bowl, salt.
Add 2 cloves garlic.
Refrigerate overnight. To serve:
Arrange on platter; sprinkle with oregano, olive oil and ground pepper.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: lo-fat gravy
directions: Blend skim milk with flour until smooth.
Blend in the broth. Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Pour water off.
Add chicken broth and some water to cover.
Add chopped onion, celery and carrot.
Add red pepper and cook until nearly done, salt and pepper finish cooking.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Reserve 1/2 cup shredded cheese and 1/2 cup pizza sauce for topping later.
In large bowl, mix remaining cheese and pizza sauce with the meat, bread crumbs and eggs.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, shape meat mixture into loaves, pressing firmly.
Bake 30 minutes.
Pour reserved sauce over top of the loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer, sprinkling with reserved cheese during last 10 minutes of baking time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ray's royal burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients into ground meat.
Shape into 8 hamburgers.
Broil, grill or fry over medium heat until done. Serve on rolls or pita bread.

title: butter mint jello
directions: Combine dry jello with pineapple (juice and all).
Add marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add crushed butter mints and Dream Whip.
Freeze; cover with foil.
Take out early enough to thaw for dessert.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together.
Heat spaghetti sauce and add to drained meat mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Layer egg noodles in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour sauce and meat mixture over noodles.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first three ingredients in electric skillet and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off and add the last three ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: cake muffins
directions: Mix all and put in ungreased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: red bell peppers pesto and shrimp
directions: In large skillet, saut peppers, carrots, celery, garlic and oregano.
Add diced tomatoes, pesto, water, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add shrimp. Cook only until shrimp turn pink. Serve over cooked and drained pasta. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese

title: carrot cake
directions: For plain flour, use 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1 teaspoon soda.
Mix all items.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Cooking Time: 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook pasta. Add other ingredients. Top with dressing. Mix well.

title: georgie's pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, cooking oil, sugar and vanilla. Add all dry ingredients. Mix well and add pecans and candied fruit. Batter will make 3 loaf pans. Grease and flour pans. Bake at 275°.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Put cranberries and sugar in a casserole and cover.
Put in oven for 20 minutes at 350° or until berries pop.
Add all other ingredients, when you remove from oven.
Keep in refrigerator. Makes a great compliment to ham or turkey.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (8 oz.) paper or plastic cups.

title: roasted corn
directions: Pull down husks without removing.
Remove silks; pull husks back into place to cover corn.
Tie with string; soak corn in cool water for 10 minutes; drain.
Place corn directly on rack in oven. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg.
Add egg, vinegar and water to sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Cook until thick.
Chill.
Serve over cabbage slaw.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple, heat juice to boiling. Pour over jello and stir until well dissolved.
Add cold water and cream cheese and beat with rotary beater until well blended.
Add pineapple, nuts and celery. Pour into molds or Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.
Serve on lettuce topped with mayonnaise and maraschino cherry.

title: ruth's fettuccine
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil on low heat until light brown. Stir in Velveeta Italiana process cheese, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Add fettuccine and mix lightly.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Serve immediately.

title: brown stone quick cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in hot water and let cool.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Cream the Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add buttermilk mixture and vanilla.
Add cocoa and water last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven at 250°.
Melt butter in shallow pan over low heat. Stir Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add Chex mix, nuts and pretzels.
Mix over low heat until all pieces are coated. Heat in oven 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread out on absorbent paper to cool.
Yield:
6 3/4 cups.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, cook shrimp (place raw shrimp in boiling water for 4 minutes); drain, peel and set aside.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Place vanilla wafer in paper muffin cup in muffin pan. Fill each about 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Top with a spoonful of pie filling.
Very easy.

title: french dip
directions: Serve with carrots and celery or chips and pretzels.
May double for large group.

title: strovali
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add in with the flour, salt and baking powder. Work together, then roll.
Cut into strips, and small pieces.
Fry and put in dish. Add honey and small confetties on top.

title: mexican bean pot
directions: Pick over beans and wash.
Place in a large saucepan and add water.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Drain fruit cocktail and reserve juice; add all but 2 Tbsp. juice to flour mixture.
Beat in egg and add vanilla.
Gently stir in fruit cocktail.
Place in well greased 8 inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour, checking at 50 minutes.

title: ruby's fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Stir to dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid.
Add juices of oranges and lemons. Add ginger ale to required strength.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion and lay in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add one tomato sauce, then cooked noodles and then other can of sauce. Next, add sausage, pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate bar and butter in a double boiler.
Beat in egg and powdered sugar; add nuts and marshmallows.
Put on wax paper; shape into log shape.
Freeze and slice.
The log can be rolled in coconut.

title: sauerkraut and pork
directions: Place sauerkraut in baking pan.
Add apples.
Place pork on sauerkraut.
Sprinkle with garlic and sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until pork is tender.

title: chocolate cookiesspringfield, missouri
directions: Melt chocolate and add the rest of the cookie ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Drain and coarsley chop artichoke hearts.
Mix artichoke hearts with remaining ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with bread or veggies. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and milk together.
Add sugar, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg.
Blend in 3 eggs and salt.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Mix apple juice and cornstarch until dissolved well and real hot.
Stir in apples, spice and Sweet 'N Low.
Pour into unbaked crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wheaties cookies(5 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in coconut.
Put Wheaties in last and stir as little as possible.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: cheddar-cranberry bagels
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon cranberry relish into cream cheese.
Spread bagel halves with cream cheese mixture.
Top with slice of cheese and turkey.
Garnish with additional relish.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Prepare
the
first
3	ingredients
and refrigerate in covered
container	for 24 hours.
Drain.
Add sugar and vinegar. Let stand 24 hours again in refrigerator.
Then put in a freezer container and freeze.

title: chili
directions: While browning meat, sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour when almost done.
Quickly cover with hot water and stir.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix and stir all of the ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
This cake will fall.

title: german pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Sift dry ingredients together. Stir in softened margarine. Add milk and vanilla.
Mix to dampen flour. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed by mixer. Add eggs, yolk and chocolate. Beat 1 minute longer.
Grease and flour tube and sides of a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and let cool completely before glazing.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Sear chops on both sides in a little hot oil.
Add veggies, tomato soup and about 1/4 cup water to rinse can.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until veggies are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients all together.
Mix milk, beaten egg and shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle parmesan
directions: Combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and eggs.
Mix together applesauce, cinnamon, mace and ginger; add.
Combine flours, salt and baking soda.
Add raisins.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2 pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn out and cool on rack.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl; add pudding mix and mix well.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Set in refrigerator to chill.

title: spaghetti or pizza sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and parsley in olive oil until onion is lightly browned.
Puree tomatoes in blender; mix in oregano and comino.
Add to sauteed mixture.
Add basil (the more you add, the sweeter the sauce).
Simmer for 2 hours on low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: curried poached fish
directions: Place in a microwave dish and cook on Medium-high in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: shirley's rice pudding
directions: Put first five ingredients into pot on low flame.
Stir frequently for two hours until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add egg that's been beaten with 1/4 cup milk.
Pour into serving dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: light dessert
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large skillet, stirring well. Place over medium heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in cherries.
Place rum in a small long handled pan, heat just until warm.
Ignite with a long match, and pour over cherry mixture.
Stir gently until flame dies down.
Serve immediately over 1/3 cup portions of ice milk.
Yields 6 servings, 182 calories and 1.9 g fat per serving.

title: creamy dill dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: firehouse jambalaya
directions: Heat 3-quart saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat until hot.
Add sausage, bell pepper, yellow onion and celery.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until the sausage is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat; add rice and red pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until the rice is browned.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix cooked spaghetti with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Pat into bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine onion and sour cream; spoon over spaghetti.
Combine meat, tomato paste and water.
Pour over cream/onion mix.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pre-school's favorite butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Beat eggs and add to creamed mixture.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add flavorings, mixing well.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll thin on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes and bake on greased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookie should appear only slightly browning around edges.
This recipe will make 60 to 75 cookies.

title: butterscotch cream cheese delight
directions: Cream confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pinon bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and spices.
Stir in nuts.
Mix together other ingredients and add to flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Pour batter into two greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool on rack.

title: busy day lemon cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft, blend in 1/2 c. milk.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with egg beater just until well mixed, about 1 minute.
(Do not overbeat.)

title: unleavened bread
directions: Mix all together until it resembles cornmeal.
Add just enough water to hold together.
Roll very thin; cut into squares, if desired, or portion with a melon baller and roll thin.
Place on a greased sheet.
Bake at 325° about 15 minutes or until edges start to brown.
Makes about 12 circles.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Put over salad.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix well the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add the dry ingredients and mix.
Add the vanilla and carrots.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in loaf pan.

title: amish friendship bread starter and bread
directions: For starter:
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a deep glass or plastic container.
Stir in remaining water, flour and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Cover with loose fitting cover.

title: western omelet
directions: Melt margarine in pie plate in microwave for 20 seconds.
Mix eggs, ham, onion and green pepper; pour into pie plate.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 2 minutes and 30 seconds to 3 minutes and 30 seconds, pushing cooked edge of omelet to center after 1 minute and 30 seconds, until center is set.
Fold and slice onto plate; salt and pepper.
Just before folding, sprinkle with 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese, if you like.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and coconut extract together.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in biscuit mix and spud flakes.
Cover bowl. Chill for 1 hour.
Form into marble-size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 to 14 minutes at 375°.

title: swann's chicken
directions: Use as many frozen chicken patties as you will need to serve. Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Cover each patty with prepared spaghetti sauce (1 tablespoon is about right).
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Add slice of cheese on each patty topping (spaghetti sauce).
Microwave 2 minutes on High or until cheese is beginning to melt.
This is a good meal with a salad and a drink.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and dry ingredients. Blend.
Roll out and cut out.
Bake on ungreased pan 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: spirit pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add alternately with the wine to creamed mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Blend in chopped pecans.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack.

title: butter cookies
directions: Draw butter and let congeal.
Beat butter for 10 to 15 minutes until light and fluffy. Add flour.
Work with hands until smooth. If too sticky, add a little more flour.

title: golden oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 24 muffin cups.
Combine dry cake mix, oats and salt in bowl.
Beat together milk, eggs and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon into muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with honey or jam.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix 4 ingredients together and pat on waxed paper.
May coat with 1/2 cup of chopped nuts (walnuts or pecans).
Chill, covered, in refrigerator.
(Lasts up to 5 days.)

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and allow to boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Serve warm over cake.

title: garlic sage cornish hens with wild rice
directions: Remove giblets from hens; reserve for another use.
Rinse hens under cold water and pat dry.
Split each hen in half lengthwise, using an electric knife.
Place hens, cut sides down, on a rack in a roasting pan coated with cooking spray.
Combine garlic and next 4 ingredients; rub hens with garlic mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour or until done.
Serve hens with wild rice.

title: fresh corn and crab soup
directions: Combine corn and chicken broth in large saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium high heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer mixture for 20 minutes.
Coat small skillet with spray oil; add oil and heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add onion mix, 3 1/4 cup milk and next three ingredients to corn mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Combine flour and remaining 1/2 cup milk, stirring with wire whisk until smooth. Add to corn mix and cook, stirring frequently over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in crabmeat and garnish if desired.
Yields 9 cups, 1/2 cup serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool; add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minute or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: black bean soup ole
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat until hot. Add onion, green pepper, carrot and celery; saute until tender. Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Yield:
8 cups/about 105 calories per 1 cup serving; protein 4.8; fat 2.1; carbo.
16.8; cholesterol 0; iron 1.8; sodium 164; calcium 44.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Chop eggs fine or in blender.
Combine all ingredients.
Serve over lettuce.
Will keep for 5 to 7 days.

title: dilled tuna and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions omitting any salt and fat.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside.
Combine the tuna and onion in a large bowl.
Add the pasta and toss gently.

title: broccoli-cheese-rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Defrost broccoli, drain.
Combine broccoli, butter, rice and cheese.
Combine egg, milk, spices and onion.
Stir into broccoli. Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on 70% power 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: khira raita(cucumber with yogurt)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thinly.
Put in a bowl, sprinkle with salt and chill about 1 hour. Pour off the liquid, pressing out as much as possible.
Mix garlic and ginger into yogurt, then stir in the cucumbers.
Combine thoroughly.
Taste and add more salt if necessary. Add lemon juice to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: baked rattlesnake
directions: Skin the snake; dress and wash in cold water.
