Cut into 3-inch sections and place in a large baking dish.
Cover with cream sauce and add the mushrooms, limes, basil, pepper and rosemary.
Cover tightly.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until done.
One large can sliced mushrooms may be substituted for fresh mushrooms.

title: luncheon rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar, salt and yeast in bowl.
Add egg, shortening and flour.
Knead to soft dough.
Let rise until double in bulk. Shape the dough into various rolls and let rise about 2 hours. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Add the boiling water using a spoon not the mixer.
When mixed, pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for approximately 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: scratch brownies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brownies start pulling away from sides of pan.

title: van's grilled steak
directions: Brush steaks with Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice on both sides.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Let set 1 to 2 hours. Cook on charcoal grill.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours before cooking.

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: Combine 7 ingredients in container of an electric mixer. Process on high 1 minute or until smooth.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: grandma child's coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, cornstarch, milk, sugar, flavoring and butter together until smooth.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut to taste. Pour into prebaked pie shell.

title: southern living spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches.
Combine syrup, cornstarch and spices.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Add peaches and simmer 1 minute.
Cool 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: almond delight
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a long pan.
Bake at 325°, stirring every 5 minutes, for 20 minutes.
Let the cooked ingredients cool, then put half in Pyrex dish.
Beat together instant pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put filling over the cooked mixture. Put remaining cooked mixture on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until set.

title: chicken and brown rice casserole
directions: Brown rice
in
butter.
Add
soups
and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in
mushrooms.
Put chicken and rice in casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: water chestnut sauce
directions: Combine stock, soy sauce, water chestnuts, onion and pimento in saucepan; set aside.
Combine cornstarch and cold water to make a paste; add to liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Makes 3 cups.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, to mix. Add vanilla wafers and baking powder. Add milk, coconut and pecans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will be quite thick. Bake in greased tube pan about 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: angel food cake
directions: Layer angel food cake in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix one 3 ounce package of pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and pour immediately over cake and part of the Heath bars before it sets up.
Then do another layer the same way, saving a few tablespoons of crushed candy to sprinkle on top.
After the second layer of cake and pudding, spread on the Cool Whip and then the last of the candy.

title: mexican rice
directions: In medium saucepan, saute pepper and onion in oil.
Add broth, salsa and corn; bring to a boil.
Add rice, flake with a fork and reduce heat to low.
Cover. Cook 15 to 20 minutes until rice is tender.
Serve garnished with cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jean marzetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Then add mushrooms, 1/2 of the cheese, tomatoes and macaroni.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: maggie crump's cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip, nuts, Amaretto and vanilla.
Pour in pie crust.
Add cherry pie filling over this. Refrigerate overnight.

title: veal cutlets in white wine
directions: Do not use Teflon pan.
Sprinkle veal with salt, pepper and flour lightly.
Heat oil in pan.
When hot, brown veal thoroughly on both sides on high heat.
Remove veal.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until tender; drain excess oil.
Add white wine, scraping bottom and sides.
Boil until all particles on bottom of pan are dissolved.
Return veal to pan; simmer until veal is tender.
Serves 4.

title: goof balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add melted oleo.
Mix and form into balls.
Melt paraffin with chocolate chips over low heat.
Keep chocolate on simmer while dipping balls.
Put balls on wax paper to harden.
If chocolate hardens too fast, add a little more paraffin.

title: five minute pie
directions: Beat first four ingredients, then stir in drained pineapple. Sometimes I add coconut and pecans to half of mixture. Pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate pie.

title: pea casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Blend in flour and salt. Add liquid from mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Mix mushrooms, water chestnuts and peas in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon sauce over.
Mix gently.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: watcha-ma-callits
directions: Blend peanut butter and oleo over low heat until smooth.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix together and let cool.
Form into balls or egg shapes.
Let dry overnight.
Dip into milk chocolate and let dry.

title: baked chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Brush chicken with salad dressing. Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: revetta's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt,
Accent, thyme, and basil.
Cut chicken into 2 inch strips.
Dip in butter mixture.
Roll in cheese and crushed cornflakes.
Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Place chicken on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: layered english pea casserole
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons margarine and flour until blended, then add milk or broth and salt to taste.
Cook until thickened.
Add drained English peas and toss until mixed.
Pour juice into jar and refrigerate.
Pour mixture into Pam sprayed 9 x 3-inch casserole dish.
Layer onion, carrots and cheese.
Mix 1/4 cup melted Shedd's Spread and cracker crumbs; spread on top of vegetable cheese mix. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
If you want to reheat later, pour some of the pea juice over the casserole and heat in microwave.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, eggs, onion and tomatoes.
Add 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Put the mixture in baking pan and pat into a loaf.
Put the other half can of tomato sauce on top of loaf and spread it evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain grease. Pour jar of Pepperidge Farm gravy on meat loaf and bake 15 minutes.

title: pandowdy(1860 recipe)
directions: Pare, core and slice thin sour, juicy apples.
Butter a deep baking dish or pan and put in a layer of apples.
Sweeten with brown sugar and flavor with lemon peel.
Strew over a layer of bread crumbs and bits of butter.
Repeat this until dish is nearly full, finishing with a layer of bread crumbs, bits of butter and a sprinkle of brown sugar.
Bake until the apples are soft.

title: lazy style baked beans
directions: Place beans into dish.
Add brown sugar, ketchup, bacon, mustard and liquid smoke with wieners.
Mix lightly.
Cut up onion into mixture.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Remove cover last half of baking.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and pack cucumbers tightly in pint or quart jars.
Add 1/2 head of dill and piece of stem, about 1 inch long, to bottom and top of quart jar (for pints use smaller amount of dill).
Add red pepper.
Bring salt, vinegar and water to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal jars and place in boiling water bath.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Saute ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour, or until rice is tender and mixture is bubbly. Sprinkle chow mein noodles over top.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in a moderate oven of everyday life, using as fuel all the grudges of the past.
Cool; turn onto a platter of cheerfulness and garnish with laughter.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first three ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick.
Set off heat.
Add vanilla.
Let set a short time. Beat until thick.
Drop on wax paper.

title: sauerbraten(braised beef; yield:  6 servings)
directions: Exchanges:
1 bread-starch exchange and 1 meat low-fat exchange.

title: lemon meat
directions: Stir-fry meat until almost done in 1 teaspoon cooking oil. Then add your remaining ingredients (2 squeezed lemons, 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper, 1 sliced onion and 2 sliced cucumbers). Simmer until desired tenderness and serve over your choice of rice or mashed potatoes.

title: pimento and cheese spread
directions: Heat cheese and milk until melted.
Cool.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Sprinkle salt; add pimento and egg.
Cook until thick. Stir all the time this is cooking.
Add 1 pint or less salad dressing.
Blend until smooth.
Good as a sandwich spread or as an appetizer.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute meat and onion until brown.
Drain excess fat.
Break meat into small pieces.
Add next five ingredients and simmer 50 minutes.
Pour into colander to separate meat from juice.
Add olives to meat.
Dip each tortilla in sauce.
Put meat on tortilla and roll.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan individual
directions: Trim eggplant; cut in 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Layer slices in colander; set over bowl and sprinkle each layer lightly with salt. Let drain one hour.
Cook garlic in small saucepan in oil over medium heat until golden brown (1 minute).
Remove garlic. Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat 2 jelly roll pans with cooking spray. Place eggplant slices in a single layer.
Brush with garlic oil. Bake for 15 minutes, until lightly brown and tender.

title: summer quick dessert
directions: Make jello according to package directions and allow to set. Mix set jello with Cool Whip with mixer.
Put into individual serving containers and chill.

title: ho-ho cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Roll into balls and chill.
Dip into melted chocolate and paraffin.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix with the corn, peas, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper, green pepper and onion.
Mix the cornmeal, flour, egg and water; pour over meat mixture.
Bake until brown.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Mix together sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken and stir. Mix together melted butter and Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters, saving liquid and rinse by hand.
Heat milk and margarine until it begins to steam lightly. Do not boil!
Add oysters, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until oysters curl at edges, then serve.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Spread in an ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa and hot water; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake is set.
Serve warm or cool, topped with cream or whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tourtiere
directions: Combine above and cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Cool. Pour into pastry-lined deep pie plate.
Cover with pastry and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and pineapple juice. Add enough water to make 1 gallon of punch. Chill and serve.

title: country dessert
directions: Roll out crackers. Save 4 tablespoons for topping.
Mix together with melted oleo and press into 10-inch pie dish.
Beat together pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and Cool Whip.
Beat until mixed well.
Pour over crust.
Garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in boiler.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat and add margarine, then add oatmeal and nuts.
Drop out on wax paper from a teaspoon.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and bake on a greased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn on a wet towel and sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Cool until just warm.

title: triscuits snacks
directions: Place cheese over crackers.
Microwave for 30 seconds. Sprinkle with seasoned pepper.
Excellent snack.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, bisquick and room temp cheese together. May need to add a few drops of water. Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes. Makes about 50 balls. Freezes well.

title: pecan cheese rounds
directions: Grate cheese while cold.
Leave cheese and margarine out until room temperature.
Mix with mixer until well blended.
Add flour, pecans and cayenne pepper.
Mix until blended.
Divide into 4 (1-inch) rolls.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Slice.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Place margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High (100%) for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until melted.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Microwave on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until thickened.
Stir several times during the last half of cooking time to prevent lumping.
Stir in cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup for top.
Add cooked macaroni.
Cover with a tight fitting lid or plastic wrap. Microwave on Medium (50%) power for 12 to 14 minutes or until heated throughout.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Remove from microwave and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Recipe yields 6 servings.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients until dough is at a consistency where it can be dropped by spoonfuls.
You may add more milk if needed. Bake in preheated oven at 425°
for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread margarine over each biscuit after they have browned.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients with blender or electric mixer.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Put green tomatoes through a meat grinder.
Cover with cold water and cook until soft.
Drain all juice from tomatoes and let stand in cold water for 1/2 hour.
Drain again.
Add brown sugar, raisins, cooked beef, orange, lemon, unpeeled apples, vinegar, coffee, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt to taste.
Put all ingredients through meat grinder.
Add to cooked tomatoes and cook about 2 hours or until tender.

title: protose
directions: Stir peanut butter, water and soy sauce until smooth.
Then add tomato juice and crackers and seasonings.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk real good. When smooth, add rest of milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and flavoring.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and chopped vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour or more.
Makes enough for 2 dozen buns.

title: barbecue beef crescent roll
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add barbecue sauce. Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet. Arrange ground beef mixture down center of dough. Sprinkle with cheese. Fold dough over top and pinch seam together. Cook at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: noodle pudding(kugel)
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Beat together eggs, sugar, cottage cheese, sour cream, milk, butter and vanilla.
Add to noodles. Stir in the raisins.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish and vegetable chowder
directions: Cook bacon in saucepan until crisp; remove bacon.
Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add 4 cups water, haddock, potatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk and bacon. Heat to serving temperature.

title: white chili
directions: Wash beans and let soak for awhile.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and chicken broth.
Cook slow for about 3 hours or until beans are done.
This can be served with sour cream and Mozzarella cheese.

title: bierox
directions: Brown meat and onion together and drain.
Shred cabbage (not too fine)
and
add
to
meat mixture.
Add seasonings to taste. Let
cool.	Using
your
favorite
bread dough recipe, shape dough to	desired
size,	as
thin as possible.
You may find a saucer helpful by stretching the dough over it.
Spoon cabbage and
meat mixture
into dough and fold over, pinching edges together.
Bake to a golden brown as you would hot rolls or light bread, about 25 minutes in 425° oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix on pineapple.
Mix in marshmallows and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth.
May add 3/4 cup chopped peanuts, if desired.
(Use chunky peanut butter and omit peanuts.)
Pack into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
When firm, cut into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: baked chicken over rice
directions: Cut small bite size chicken breast (boneless or cut off bone) to generously cover bottom of baking dish.
Add drained pineapple over the chicken, then the Russian salad dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This will be juicy.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter roast
directions: Cook rice.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May substitute extra cracker or bread crumbs for eggs.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar and Pet milk together for 2 minutes at a boil.
Have ready the sifted confectioners sugar.
Beat in sugar until smooth.
If frosting gets too thick, add a small amount of milk.
Spread between layers of cake.
Plenty for sides and top.
Enough frosting for 3 layer cake.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Put apples
and
1 cup sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil. Mix sugar and flour in bowl, add water to the thickness you want (about like a cake batter).
Put
butter in pan, heat in oven until melted and hot.
Pour batter in center of melted butter. Pour the hot apples in
center
of
batter.
Bake
at 450° until done.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixed with sugar on top.

title: caramel bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place sugar in bottom of a buttered glass dish.
Tear bread slices into quarters and place on top of sugar.
Mix all other ingredients (except nutmeg) and pour over the bread.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve hot with milk or half and half.

title: black-eyed peas casserole
directions: Layer ground beef; mix with onions and pepper in bottom of glass casserole dish. Mix peas and tomatoes together and pour over ground beef. Mix cornbread according to package and pour over peas and tomatoes. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass cake dish in microwave oven (about 30 seconds at High).
Mix brown sugar into melted butter. Cook, uncovered, until brown sugar melts (about 2 minutes at High).
Arrange pineapple slices and maraschino cherries in dish.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1 cup warm water; let stand about 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion, parsley, salt, marjoram and pepper in butter or margarine until onion is tender, but not brown. Blend in flour. Stir in the milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Stir in sweet potatoes. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes. Slowly blend in sweet potato mixture. Fold into egg whites.
Gently pour into a 1-quart souffle dish. Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut and nuts together.
Spread evenly in the bottom of a buttered pan (oblong pan 13 1/2 x 10). Mix cake mix by instructions on back of box.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine.
Blend cream cheese and margarine together.
Gradually add powdered sugar to cream cheese and margarine mixture.
Mix well and spoon on top of cake.
(Do not spread.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour enough maple syrup to cover the bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Then sprinkle enough cinnamon to completely cover the syrup. If desired, chopped walnuts and raisins can be added.
Add 1 package of Pillsbury big country biscuits.
Press each biscuit into the syrup-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until golden.
Turn onto dinner plate and serve warm.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: chicken zamboanga(serves 4)
directions: In large shallow baking pan, place chicken skin side up in single layer.
In bowl, mix undiluted soup, cream cheese, olives and ginger.
Spread mixture evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle curry on chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until fork-tender.
To serve, place chicken on rice and pour soup mixture over all.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Serve with chips or fresh cut vegetables.

title: molasses oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal, let stand one hour. Mix 2 cups of the flour, yeast and salt. Heat molasses, honey and oil to lukewarm, and stir in dry ingredients. Stir in oatmeal and beat until smooth. Add beaten eggs and nuts. Mix in enough of remaining flour to make dough stiff enough to handle. Knead well. Let rise in covered bowl until double in bulk. Divide into 3 loaf pans. Let rise again. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.

title: low fat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: marinated round steak
directions: Poke meat with a fork.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over the meat and marinate overnight.
Turn meat over and baste in a.m. Continue to marinate until ready to grill. Grill approximately 20 minutes.

title: creamy horseradish sauce
directions: Beat cream in a small bowl with mixer until soft peaks form. Fold in horseradish, sugar, salt and pepper.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Refrigerate.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine pineapple and juice with gelatin. Bring to boil in saucepan, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool completely. Stir in buttermilk and fold in whip topping. Pour into 2 1/2-quart Pyrex dish. Cover and chill overnight.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut mushroom stems out of caps.
Dice mushroom stems and onion. Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain sausage, all except 2 tablespoons of grease.
Saute onion and sausage in grease.
Mix mushroom mixture, bread crumbs and cheese.
Stuff mushroom caps and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mary dudderar gooch's spanish rice
directions: Cook rice.
Brown ground beef, onions and celery.
Remove from flame and add tomatoes, pimientos and rice.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, 1/2 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: appetizer dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, fruit cocktail, pecans and dry jello.
Stir and mix well.
Sprinkle few pecans on top and store in refrigerator several hours or overnight before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Pour mixture of all ingredients into a 1-gallon freezer and freeze.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until mushy.
Drain.
Add ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Soak beans in water for 2 to 4 hours. Drain and rinse beans. Brown diced bacon until medium done. With slotted spoon, remove from grease.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add enough water to cover ingredients.
Turn crock-pot on high setting until starts to boil, then turn on low setting.
Let cook for 8 to 10 hours or until beans are tender.
(I start beans the night before and let cook all night.)

title: potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in the skins in boiling salted water until tender, but not mushy.
Peel them while still hot and let them cool to room temperature.
Slice and arrange slightly overlapping on a serving plate.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix together margarine, water and cocoa. Bring to a boil. Mix flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, salt and soda together into another bowl. When first mixture comes to a boil, pour into sugar-flour mixture. Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: zesty pasta
directions: Cook pasta (30 seconds), drain with cold water. Add 1/2 cup Zesty dressing. Add diced vegetables and whole olives. Add McCormick Salad Supreme. Add rest of bottle of Zesty. Refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together into mixing bowl flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut butter in hand until fine crumbs are formed.
Stir in buttermilk gently until all ingredients are moist and dough is formed.
Chill 45 minutes.
Roll 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425°, until golden brown.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; add sugar and the egg yolks, beaten with the water.
Cook slowly until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
When cool, fold in the stiffly beaten whites.
Line the bottom and sides of a spring-form with split ladyfingers.
Trim, if necessary, to fit and arrange rounded side toward pan.
Add a layer of filling; cover with ladyfingers and repeat to fill mold.
Chill overnight.
When ready to serve, remove sides of form and place on serving platter.
Top with whipped cream.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain and put into saucepan with 6 cups boiling water and boil slowly for 2 hours or until soft.
Add onion and bacon which have been fried light brown.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: pecan cake(no bake)
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix all ingredients together and swish a little water around in milk can to get it all and also give extra moisture.
Pack into tube pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate 2 days.
Cut with very sharp knife.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Blend dressing with cream cheese.
Form into one large ball or 2 small balls.
Roll balls in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: merle haggard's honky tonk man's beer pancakes(celebrity recipe)
directions: Beat egg yolks with the sugar.
Stir in buttermilk, mixed with baking soda.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add mixture alternately with beer.
Stir in melted butter.
In large bowl, beat egg whites with dash of salt until they form stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites gently into yolk mixture.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk and cherry juice.
Add flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Cook until soft ball stage. Take off stove; let stand 5 minutes.
Add nuts.
Beat with wooden spoon until thickened.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add butter, cottage cheese, salt, onion, corn and broccoli to beaten eggs, then gradually add corn bread mix.
Moisten well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in microwave, then stir in nuts and noodles. Mix well. Spoon onto wax paper and allow to cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix and pour over bread arranged in baking pan and let set for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; chill until begins to thicken. Beat with a rotary eggbeater until fluffy, gradually beating in milk until a thick, fluffy mixture results.
Fold in fruit.
Any kind of fruit in season may be used, as well as drained, canned fruit.
Pile in sherbet glasses and chill until firm or may be served on slices of plain or sponge cake, or sandwiched between small commercial cookies and chilled.

title: squash pecan casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Mix with sugar, egg, mayonnaise, grated cheese, butter and bread crumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with pecans.
Cook at 375°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: In large bowl, mix cabbage, pimentos, green pepper and onion. Combine in saucepan and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick: sugar, vinegar, water and mustard seed.
Pour over cabbage mix and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Slaw will keep several days.

title: homemade baileys
directions: Dissolve coffee in 1/2 C. hot water.
Cool.
Add the rest of ingredients and blend until smooth.
Store tightly in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Stir before serving.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In brown paper bag, combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika and beef cubes.
Shake well to coat.
Brown meat in butter; add onions, garlic, pepper and simmer until well coated.
Empty all into large Dutch oven.
Dissolve bouillon cubes (3) in 3 cups boiling water.
Add to Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling point, then lower to simmer; cover and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add rest of vegetables and additional 5 cups boiling water with the dissolved 5 bouillon cubes and tomato puree.
Bring to a second boil, lower heat and cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes. Additional bouillon stock may be added if too thick.

title: stir-fry meal
directions: In a large skillet cook onions in oil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick crust
directions: Melt
butter
in
a microwave-safe bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and add
favorite fruit.
Makes a quick and delicious cobbler type dessert.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs on both sides with salt and pepper; place in a shallow roasting pan.
Lay onion slices over ribs.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour; baste occasionally, turning ribs twice.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix in remaining ingredients, adding grated carrots gradually, while mixing at medium speed.
Pour batter into 3 floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes - do not overbake.

title: pasties
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in quickly the lard until pieces of the mixture are very fine.
Add water a little at a time until mixture sticks together.
Do not add too much water. Handle mixture as little as possible.
Cut dough int five portions.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain peaches, pears and pineapple and reserve juice.
Pour juice into medium saucepan.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and curry powder.
Add to juice.
Stir and cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Stir fruit into hot mixture and cook until thoroughly heated.
Prepare ahead and heat in oven or microwave later if desired.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: corn dog twists
directions: Do not cut cucumbers until you take them out of vinegar.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow directions of Solomon for bringing up a child in Proverbs 23:14 which is "Beat him with a rod."
This is a simple cake baked best as a loaf for 50 minutes.
Slices best after a few hours of cooling.

title: cheesy-broccoli bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Put bread crumbs on top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: latvian bacon buns
directions: Cook bacon.
Drain and cut or break into small pieces.
Cook the onion in the bacon drippings.
Mix onion and bacon together. Put spoonful of bacon and onion mixture onto center of crescent roll.
Roll up the crescent roll and seal.
Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 375° until done, about 10 minutes.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix garlic and other herbs in with meat.
Add all other ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: chicken, broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and cauliflower in a casserole dish; top with 1 1/2 cups chicken.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese, 1 tablespoon butter and 2 tablespoons dry bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon crisp
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Press half of mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and hot water.
Cook and stir until thick and boiling for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir small amount into egg yolks and return to hot mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in lemon peel and juice.
Pour over baked crumb crust; top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: greek isles appetizers(makes 70 meatballs)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, eggs, onion, garlic and seasonings in large bowl until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs on rack in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with Cucumber Sauce.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze at least 1 hour before serving.

title: date rice krispies cookies
directions: Cook dates, sugar, butter or margarine and egg together slowly.
Stir constantly until well mixed.
Cool.
Add to mixture the vanilla, chopped pecans and Rice Krispies.
Blend.
Roll into balls and shape into logs.
Roll in ground nuts, coconut or powdered sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
If logs, slice into cookies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish; then pour into mixture of all ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon swirl bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Blend together shortening, honey and salt; set aside.
Heat milk until bubbles around edge.
Mix together with shortening, honey, salt, yeast and water.
Gradually add flour and oats, stirring with spoon.
When completely mixed, set aside with damp cloth to cover bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out on floured wax paper; roll to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
With fork, mix together brown sugar, almonds, raisins, flour, butter and cinnamon. Mixture should be crumble texture.
Lightly spread by hand over dough.
Starting at left edge, roll bread dough with filling; roll to right edge.
Place in greased and floured bread/loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and pour in bowl. Add onion, celery and pimento.

title: easy lasagna # 1
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook meat, stirring until lightly brown.
Drain meat and return to skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine cottage or Ricotta cheese, egg, salt and pepper.

title: iowa boiled beef dinner
directions: Place meat in a large pot.
Add salt, peppercorns, bay leaf and water.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat; let any fat rise to top of broth.
Skim; return meat to pot. Cut off a band of skin around middle of each potato.
Place potatoes, onions and carrots around meat in pot.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender.

title: german casserole
directions: Layer bottom of casserole with ground beef, noodles, corn, soup and cheese.
Heat in oven until hot.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Spread preserves over bottom of a well-greased 9-inch round cake pan and sprinkle with nuts. Separate biscuits and dip in melted margarine. Place 12 of the biscuits overlapping around outer edge of bottom of pan. Use remaining 6 biscuits to make an inner circle. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Turn out of pan immediately.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Simmer vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add remaining ingredients.
Boil 10 minutes.
Seal in canning jars.

title: peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine peanut butter and corn syrup; add Rice Krispies and coat well.
Press mixture into pie pan.
Spread ice cream into crust and freeze.
Good served with fruit or hot chocolate.

title: chips ahoy brownie pie
directions: Cut 5 cookies in half; set aside.
Finely roll remaining cookies.
Combine cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine. Press on bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Then put dough on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Then fold in whipped topping. Spread mixture on crust. Next, combine strawberries with glaze and put on top.
If desired, add nuts and powdered sugar on top.

title: california casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large skillet; add beef and brown.
Drain fat.
Add garlic, onion, green pepper, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce, then add tomatoes, drained kidney beans and rice; stir to blend.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.

title: french onion stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, celery and carrots in a 3-quart casserole.
Combine the rest (except potatoes) and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 1 hour longer.
Stir occasionally.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs. Add 1 tablespoon sugar for each egg yolk.
Beat. Add brandy. Beat whites.
Whip the cream.
Add yolks to egg nog. Mix, then add whipping cream.
Fold in egg whites. Dip from the bottom.
Serves 20.

title: meatball dinner
directions: Soften bread in milk. Stir. Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Mix. Add ground beef; mix well. Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in flour and brown.
Drain off excess fat. Add tomato juice, water, carrots (drained), salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine the peaches with 1 cup of sugar.
Let stand.
Put the batter in a 2-quart casserole.
Place in the oven to melt. Combine the remaining sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this over the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon the peaches on top of the batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Any kind of fruit can be used in this cobbler, fresh or canned.

title: fudge ecstasies
directions: In
a
heavy
medium
size
saucepan, heat 1 cup of the chocolate chips, unsweetened chocolate and margarine or butter until
melted, stirring constantly.
Transfer to a large mixer bowl to cool slightly.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add	eggs,
sugar
and vanilla to the chocolate mixture and beat
well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed. Stir in	remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful
on lightly greased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Edges are firm and surface is dull and cracked.) Cool on sheet for 1 minute.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add orange juice.
Chill until thick (jelly like).
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.

title: peach jam with pectin(sugar-free)
directions: Crush peaches in saucepan; stir in sweetener, fruit pectin, lemon juice and ascorbic acid.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Continue to stir 2 minutes.
Pour into freezer containers.
Cover and freeze.

title: gingerbreadgroves, texas
directions: Beat sugar, syrup, eggs and oil.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except macaroni.
Alternate layers of macaroni and meat mixture in deep 2 quart casserole. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Put crushed potato chips on top, if desired. This dish may be mixed together, instead of layered.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine juice from beets, vinegar and sugar into a bowl; stir well.
Add beets and eggs.
Refrigerate.

title: orange carrot cake with buttercream icing(heritage recipe)
directions: heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
In large bowl, blend all cake ingredients, beat two minutes at high speed. Pour into greased pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool before removing pan.

title: roast for asking
directions: Mix all ingredients well and fill greased loaf pan, coated with sesame seed.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Line a 2-quart Pyrex dish with lettuce.
Lay ingredients in order as listed.
Put in the refrigerator.

title: hot win mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Store mix in an airtight container.
To serve, combine 2 teaspoons mix and 1/2 cup water in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add 1 cup wine and heat thoroughly (do not boil).
Serve with a cinnamon stick, if desired.
Makes about 72 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa. Add alternately with the milk, mixing well after each addition. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Cool in pan on cake rack for 5 minutes before removing from pan.
It may take a little longer than 1 hour to bake.

title: vegi chili pie
directions: Soak TVP in soy beef seasoning overnight in 2 cups warm water. Mix cornbread ingredients (cornmeal, baking soda, flour, eggs, milk and vegetable oil.)

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with broccoli.
Dip chicken pieces in soup mixture and place on top of broccoli.
Pour remaining soup on top.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Soak bread cubes in melted butter and place on top of soups.
Sprinkle generously with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate satin pie
directions: Whisk together evaporated milk and egg yolks in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is very hot and thickens slightly.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in morsels until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is very smooth.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm. Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nuts.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt margarine; dip pieces of chicken in margarine.
Roll in crushed chips.
Bake in a shallow pan lined with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Stir in butter.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once; stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut into six 6-inch squares.
Place apple in center of each; sprinkle each generously with cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Moisten edges of squares and fold corners to center; pinch together.
Place one inch apart in an 11 1/2 x 7-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey-glazed turkey
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Using cold water, rinse turkey inside and out; blot dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle body and neck cavities with salt (if desired).
On rack in shallow large baking pan, brush turkey with honey, covering completely.
In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in garlic, red peppers, sugar, thyme, onion, lemon-pepper seasoning and bouillon; generously baste turkey with mixture.
Pour hot water into bottom of pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Cover turkey with tent of heavy-duty aluminum foil.

Continue roasting about 20 minutes per pound for stuffed turkey or 16 minutes unstuffed, basting with pan drippings about every 15 minutes until bird is brown, juices in inner thigh run clear when pricked and instant-read meat thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh (without touching bone) registers 180°.
Transfer turkey to serving platter; garnish as desired.
Let rest 15 to 30 minutes before carving.
Makes 24 four-ounce servings of turkey with gravy.

title: huckleberry pie
directions: Place
1 cup berries, sugar, water, cornstarch and lemon juice in sauce pan. Simmer 3 to 4 minutes until smooth and clear. Cool slightly.
Place 3 cups berries on cool pie crust. Add the cooked mixture. Cool and serve with
Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole ii
directions: Mix together the chicken soup, milk and Cheez Whiz; cook on low heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour rice and broccoli in mixture. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until mixture is set, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot and spicy avocado dip
directions: Peel avocado and slice in bowl.
Remove seed.
Smash avocado well with fork or processor.
Add Picante sauce and mix well until blended.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.
Use chips of your choice to eat dip and enjoy.

title: beef noodle dish
directions: Cook cubed eye of round in pressure cooker for 10 minutes. Put beef and broth in 3-quart Tupperware casserole dish for microwave.
Mix up gravy mix and 2 cups water.
Add to beef and broth.
Season with seasoned salt.
Serve over top of alfredo noodles, prepared according to package directions.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Mix dry ingredients. Mix both together. Add whatever you want to this batter (chocolate chips, raisins, cut up prunes, M&M's). Crushed cereal (boxed) can be substituted for part of the oats. Cinnamon adds a nice flavor. (I call this create-a-cookie!) Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Fry in oil and margarine until golden brown.
Put in bake dish;
cover with sauce.
Using 2 tablespoons margarine, saute onion until clear.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 325°.
Cover while baking.

title: green tomato jelly
directions: Puree cut green tomatoes in blender.
Boil tomatoes and sugar for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 (3 ounce) package jello.
Beat well until jello has dissolved.
Pour into jelly glasses.
Cool, then top with paraffin wax or process using water bath method.
(Cherry flavored jello makes this especially good!)

title: one dish chicken and rice
directions: Put mushroom soups in large baking pan.
Fill each empty can with water and add to pan.
Add rice and stir well.
Lay chicken pieces over mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove foil for last 15 minutes of baking time. Delicious!!

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets; save 1 cup beet juice.
Add other ingredients and pour over beets.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps several days.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides with a little shortening on medium high. Cover with water; turn down to low; simmer for several hours until tender. Mix soups together; pour over roast. Peel and quarter onion and potatoes. Scrape carrots and cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces. Add ingredients to roast to flavor. Cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: hot cran-apple salad
directions: Place cranberries and apples in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Combine oats, chopped nuts, brown sugar and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of fruit.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Stir until mixture begins to thicken.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients into large mixing bowl first.
Then add Crisco, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla flavoring.
Mix until creamy. Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Cook for 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo and coloring; stir well.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yield: 2 to 3 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Broil chicken until done.
Remove the skin and take the chicken off the bone. Put this in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat together 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 cup of milk. Pour on top of chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top of mixture. Heat 2 cups of chicken broth and 1/2 stick of butter.
Pour over the stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Grease a spring form pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Do not pre-heat oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave in oven until cool.

title: heavenly chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until fluffy and pour on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk and pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then cover with plain
Cool Whip before serving.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine; pour over flour and 1/2 cup of pecans.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat mixture in bottom.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom layer.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Note:
Chicken may be substituted for beef.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in about 1 cup milk.

Put meats of choice, cheese of choice and vegetables (you may want other vegetables as well, or instead of - experiment!!) on top of unbaked pie shells. Pour egg mixture over the vegetables, meats and cheeses in pie shell.
Add more milk if necessary to fill pie shell, stirring it to blend in.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until "set."

title: meat and noodle skillet
directions: In a large skillet lightly brown beef and sausage.
Add onion, garlic, salt, pepper, basil, tomato paste, water and mushrooms. Stir well and add noodles.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until the noodles are tender, stirring gently two or three times with a fork.
Before serving, stir in Blue cheese and walnuts.
Serve from skillet.
Serves 6.

title: greek rice
directions: Combine in large bowl all ingredients.
Put into large casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour.

title: hot meatballs
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients.
Make small bite sized balls of meat.
Simmer in a skillet until done.
Then add 2 jars of jelly and 2 bottles of chili sauce.
Let stew for about an hour before serving.
Make sure you use the long skewers to serve with.

title: noel cake (good yellow cake)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt; cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Add flavoring. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and blend well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased loaf pan.
Cool.

title: easy lemon chess pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Add butter, milk and lemon juice. Stir well. Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Fix pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate according to package directions. Flute edges. Pour filling mixture into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pie is just set. Let cool on a wire rack. Chill. Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: peach crisp
directions: Pour peaches into pan.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter until lightly browned.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix together and add pecans.
Heat in 325° oven for 25 minutes until bubbling.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: refrigerator crock salad
directions: Grind, chop or shred vegetables.
Add celery seed and soak in salt water for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables.
Put in crock or covered container and let stand in refrigerator.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in bowl.
Prepare dressing of mayonnaise and sugar.
Make a day ahead; cover in refrigerator.

title: molasses fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix soda with molasses until it foams.
Add to first mixture.
Sift flour and spices.
Add alternately with milk.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to raisins and dates; mix well.
Add nuts and batter.
Bake in two 8-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix well; serve chilled.

title: company chicken
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Blend together soup, cream cheese, salt, cottage cheese and milk.
Layer noodles, chicken, onions, peppers, parsley, olives and liquid.
Top with buttered bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: danish pudding
directions: Take 3/4 flour and mix with dates and nuts.
Mix with ingredients, bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine egg and milk; combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then coat with flour mixture.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Bake 1 hour.
Easy and good!

title: veggie pizza
directions: One medium size elephant is needed for this recipe.
If the elephant is too large, the meat will be tough.
Use very sharp knife.
Cut the elephant into small bite size pieces (approximately 2 months is needed to cut up the elephant).
Cook over gas fire in open pot maintaining 465° temperature for about 4 weeks.
Salt to taste. Add enough brown gravy to cover.
This recipe serves approximately 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, two rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary....most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well, adding enough chicken broth from boiling breasts to give the mixture the consistency of chicken dressing. Top with 1 stick of butter, melted, and Ritz crackers, crumbled. Cook at 350°
about 30 minutes.
Very good!
Makes a big casserole.
Can be frozen.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg with a spoon.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with hands.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot, low setting.
Stir before you leave and when you get home.
Will be done in 6 hours.
This is very good with rice.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Break up Roquefort cheese with a fork into small pieces.
(Do not use blender.)
Mash clove of garlic well with mortar and pestle.
Add equal parts vinegar and oil.
Whisk to desired consistency.
Add cheese, garlic and basil.
Stores well in a glass jar.

title: * glorified hot dogs *
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise halfway.
Spread with mustard.
Fill with pickle relish and top with cheese.
Roll in a crescent roll and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: italian baked beans
directions: Brown sausage balls and kielbasa in skillet.
Drain and put in small roasting pan.
Add all other ingredients, except bacon. Partially cook bacon and place across top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: miracle pie crust
directions: Using a fork, combine flour, shortening, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.

title: eggs strata
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Put little butter on both sides.
Mix together eggs, salt, mustard, milk and pepper with wire whisk. Refrigerate night before.

title: tourtere(meat pie)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour; stir often.
Add mashed potatoes.
Mix should be not too wet or dry.
Put in pastry.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: easy skillet supper
directions: Cut bacon in 1/2-inch pieces and fry crisp.
Cook ground beef and onion together.
After ground beef is browned, stir in soy sauce and water.
Add vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook over high heat until steam escapes.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 15 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Mix chicken with combined remaining ingredients.
Cover; microwave on High 18 minutes.
Turn dish once or twice during cooking.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Melt butter in milk.
Mix in eggs with sugar. Add flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Add milk mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 400°.

title: quick lemon pepper chicken
directions: Pour oil to cover bottom of a large skillet and cook both sides of chicken over medium heat.
Salt and pepper both sides. Cook approximately 5 minutes, until brown.
At the same time, boil rice according to directions.
Remove chicken from pan and drain grease.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Pack cucumber mixture in jars, pour juice over and put tops on.
Store all jars in refrigerator until used.
Lasts 1 1/2 to 3 months, refrigerated.

title: artichoke dip(can also be used as a side dish)
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes. Serve with "dip size" corn chips.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix flour, 2 1/2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder and poppy seed together and set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, oil, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, 1 1/2 teaspoons butter flavoring and 1 1/2 teaspoons almond flavoring together.
Gradually add flour mixture. Do not overbeat.
Pour into 4 mini loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Pour glaze over loaves and let them set for 5 minutes.
Wrap tightly in foil.

title: antelope stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook until onion is tender, then remove from skillet.
Add meat to skillet and cook until lightly browned.
Reserve 1/3 cup beef broth.
Stir in remaining broth, catsup, garlic and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend reserved broth and flour and stir into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Reduce heat and add sour cream if you wish.
Spoon mixture over noodles.

title: povitica(a croatian nut bread)
directions: Combine all ingredients as you would bread dough.
Knead well. When dough doubles in size once, cover kitchen table with cloth (pin corners tightly to table).
Sprinkle cloth very lightly with flour.
Put dough on it and pull out, with hands under dough, until it stretches to proper thickness.
Spread filling over dough.
Lift two corners of cloth and roll in jelly roll fashion.

title: special grits
directions: Cook grits, boiling water and salt until they are done (about 5 minutes and not watery).
Remove from heat and add margarine and cheese.
Beat eggs in 8 ounce measuring cup and fill cup to the top with milk.
Add this to grits mixture.
Add sugar to mixture. Cover with corn flake crumbs; dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 5 to 6 minutes before serving.
Makes 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
(Can be doubled using larger pan.)

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; sift together twice. Cream shortening and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Stir in coconut flavoring and coconut.
Pour into tube pan and place in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil for 15 minutes.
Add orange Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sunday supper soup
directions: Make meatballs:
In a bowl combine beef, egg, 3 tablespoons water, bread crumbs, salt and parsley; mix lightly.
With hands shape into 24 balls.
Brown meatballs in a 350° oven.
Drain off fat; set meatballs aside.

title: sour cream meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and place in baking pan.
Bake for one hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of square or round glass baking dish. Sprinkle with 3 herbs. Spread a layer of pizza sauce, and then a layer of Parmesan cheese and more herbs. Top with mozzarella cheese.

title: hot dried beef(appetizer)
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers or party rye or pumpernickel bread.

title: baked tofu
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place tofu on cloth and squeeze out water.
Put tofu into a mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put mixture into casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix everything together.
Add squash last.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 more minutes.

title: toffee squares
directions: In mixing bowl cream together butter and brown sugar until light.
Add egg yolk and vanilla, gradually beating in flour until smooth and blended (dough will be thick).
Spread evenly on an ungreased jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown and puffy.
Remove from oven.
Arrange chocolate bars evenly over surface, let set 5 minutes to soften.
Spread chocolate and sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: chili
directions: Brown turkey and onion in a large skillet.
Add chili and garlic powder, then add tomato and hot sauces.
Stir and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fast ground beef casserole
directions: Fry meat and onion until well browned.
Salt and pepper.
Add corn and soup.
Place mixture into greased casserole dish; spread with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Parboil beans for 2 minutes.
Set aside and let set for 1 hour.
Drain.
Bring
quarts
of
water	to
a boil.
Add beans, salt pork, onion and mixture in crock-pot.
Cover beans with boiling water.
Set on high and bake until tender.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken breasts in oil.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in pan for about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over cooked egg noodles or rice.

title: potato and garlic soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large, heavy bottomed pot and saute leeks and garlic.
Cook over low heat for several minutes. Add potatoes, broth and salt and allow to come to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes to an hour.
Remove potatoes and garlic cloves; reserve both.
Puree a small amount at a time in a blender. When smooth, return to broth.
Add water if too thick.
Add milk or cream and heat.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Serve.

title: date nut coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and soda into mixing bowl. Beat eggs slightly and add.
Blend in buttermilk and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Stir in dates and pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and almonds; sprinkle over batter.
Last, add 1/4 cup melted butter over the top of the mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: carribbean slaw
directions: In a large salad bowl, mix all ingredients together. Chill slightly before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Wash onions.
Cook in small amount of boiling water for 20 minutes or until nearly tender.
Drain.
Peel.
Slice tops off. Scoop centers out and save.
Fill onions with lima beans.
Dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Start oven at moderately hot (400°). Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place stuffed onions in prepared baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes or until tender.
Saute scooped out onion centers with crumbs in remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Spoon over onions.
Continue to bake for 5 minutes or until tops are browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sylvia's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or casserole
dish.
Top
with
potato
chip
crumbs.	Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dill pickles
directions: In each jar, put 2 dill heads, 1 clove garlic, alum (the size of a pea) and cucumbers packed tightly.
Mix water, vinegar, and salt in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand about 5 minutes; drain. Heat again.
Do this 3 times then seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding mix and cocoa with milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip for a marbled effect.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Cool Whip may be added to the top if desired to decorate.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Combine corn, beans, cheese, onion, Miracle Whip and sauce. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy candied popcorn
directions: Pop the corn as directed.
Remove any unpopped kernels.
Mix together Karo syrup, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat for 2 minutes or until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
(Do not double recipe.) Pour over the popped corn in deep kettle and stir over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until corn is evenly and completely coated.
Remove from heat and spread on greased surface or form into balls.

title: mabel's monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in fourths.
In plastic bag, put 2/3 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Shake the biscuits in bag, one tube at a time.
Place in well-greased Bundt pan in layers, 1 tube at a time.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on each tube (layer).
Melt oleo, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Make a peanut butter sandwich by spreading peanut butter between crackers.
After making up 20 to 24 cookies, melt chocolate.
Dip cookies into chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: baked creamed potatoes
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter about 5 minutes.
Stir in pimento and flour.
Add milk gradually; stir and cook until thickened.
Season to taste.
Add potatoes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
This can be prepared ahead of time, stored in refrigerator and baked before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Bake both pie shells and let cool.
Mix together until fluffy the condensed milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Fill pie shells and refrigerate.

title: greens, brazilian style(low-fat)
directions: Cut large stems from the leaves.
Roll bunches of leaves like a cigar and cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Cut until all the greens are shredded.
Boil water, add ham bouillon cubes and place greens in boiling water.
Lower heat and let simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: "cookie's" chili
directions: Brown beef, green peppers and onions.
Drain grease.
Add chili seasonings and simmer 15-20 minutes. Put mixture into Dutch oven and add tomato sauce, chili powder and kidney beans.
Cook on low heat 3-4 hours.
Add crushed peppers to taste.

title: breakfast bible class sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage and onion in heated frying pan.
Drain all grease except approximately 1 tablespoon.
Add flour and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring.
Add hot milk all at once.
Stir mixture constantly until it thickens.
Season with a little salt and lots of pepper.
Pour over split biscuits.
Homemade are best but at Bible Class they sometimes use those from a tube.
Can be made a day before and refrigerated.
Reheat slowly, adding a little more milk until of desired consistency.
This should not be too thick, just nice and creamy.

title: streusel raspberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
In small bowl, combine milk, butter and egg until blended.
Stir into flour mixture until moistened.
Spoon 1/2 batter into muffin cups, divide raspberries in cups, then top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle Pecan Streusel Topping over tops.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in greased or paper-lined cups.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lazy jane's beef casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Mix with stew meat into casserole.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Stir several times (if you're home).

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a long 9 x 13-inch sheet.

title: peanut butter crackers
directions: Put peanut butter on crackers and eat.
Jelly or Marshmallow Creme are optional.

title: cheese deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise; carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Stir yeast into warm water in a large bowl.
Heat together the milk, shortening, 1/4 cup sugar and salt to about 110°.
Add to yeast.
Beat in 1 cup flour and egg.
Beat in as much remaining flour as possible.
Knead in remaining for about 8 to 10 minutes. Place dough in a large greased bowl.
Cover with wet paper towel; let rise in warm place (85°) until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down, then turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Cover with towel again for 10 minutes.
Roll piece of dough into a 15 x 7-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll from the narrow side; pinch edges to seal.
Place the roll in a greased 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan; let rise until doubled.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients; stir over low heat until mixed and melted.
Cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to warm mixture and stir.
Add nuts and chocolate chips; mix well.
Pour into a greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of 13 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan. Spread cherry pie filling on pineapple but do not mix.
Spread dry cake mix over top and sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Slice oleo and place on top of nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn bread delight
directions: Grease large iron skillet.
Sprinkle a little cornmeal in bottom.
Brown in oven.
Pour mixture into skillet and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: quick potato salad
directions: In blender, mix the egg, garlic, oil and vinegar.
Pour over potatoes.
Add parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk cocoa cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 9 x 2-inch round cake pan (one pan only).
Mix together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda and salt.
To this, add buttermilk, vegetable oil or melted butter and vanilla.
Mix together.
Turn batter into pan; bake in middle of oven 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes, then turn out.
When cool, spread a layer of raspberry preserves on top of cake and then a layer of whipped cream.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt. Let stand overnight; drain very well. In a saucepan, cook sugar, cornstarch, celery seed, mustard, turmeric, ginger and vinegar over medium heat until fairly thick. Add zucchini mixture and the red and green peppers. Continue cooking until thick, then boil 1/2 hour, stirring frequently.

title: delicious one-dish meal
directions: Put oil in electric frypan; add meat and chopped onions. Brown lightly. Add tomatoes, corn, mushrooms and enough water to just cover. Spread noodles over top with sliced cheese. Cook in electric frypan on low heat (260°). Simmer about 1 1/2 hours. If grated cheese is used, add the last 1/2 hour. Add water if necessary.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs; add buttermilk and oil.
Mix well.
Add sugar and dry ingredients.
Add Raisin Bran and extra raisins.
Stor in refrigerator in covered container.
Mix keeps well for 6 weeks.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Spread filling in an 8 x 8-inch greased baking pan.
Combine oats, flour and brown sugar.
Work oleo in with knife or fingers. Sprinkle over filling.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Pour in baking dish.
Place three slices bacon or two tablespoons bacon drippings on top.
Bake at 350° until beginning to brown.
This is a very inexpensive dish and very much liked.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in quarters and boil until done. Drain water and cool.
While potatoes are cooling, mix in a small saucepan vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
While potatoes are still a little warm, dice them into a large bowl.
When vinegar mixture comes to a boil, pour this mixture over warm diced potatoes.
Mix the potatoes in the liquid, then pour off excess vinegar mixture. Cover and chill potatoes in fridge.
When potatoes are cold, add diced celery and parsley flakes over potatoes.
Mix in mayonnaise using folder method so as not to break the potatoes.
Paprika may be sprinkled on top before serving.

title: hummus(sandwich spread)
directions: Place garlic, parsley and onions in a food processor or blender and mince.
Add chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice and salt and puree to a thick paste.
Season to tate, if desired, with cayenne and cumin.
Transfer to a tightly lidded container and chill.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites until stiff; set aside. Cream margarine and vegetable shortening.
Add sugar and egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well; add coconut, nuts and extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured pans, 2 cups batter for each pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or test with toothpick.
Use cream cheese icing.

title: sensible salsa
directions: Wash and remove seeds from peppers.
Chop vegetables in food processor.
Heat remaining ingredients until paste and sugar are diluted.
Combine with vegetables, chill and serve.

title: western mac
directions: My sweet potato, do you carrot all for me.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Saute celery in butter until tender, yet crisp.
Mix the egg into the milk until it is well beaten.
Add all the ingredients to the bread crumbs and mix well.
Bake in a shallow greased pan at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until mixture is as dry as you like it. It will dry a little after removed from the oven.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix 3 ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, onions, eggs and pepper with fork.
Add cracker crumbs.
Roll in more cracker crumbs and pat loosely. Cook in deep fat until golden brown.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Put batter in funnel and drop in pretzel-like pattern in 2 inches of melted Crisco or cooking oil.
Cook at 375° until golden brown, holding finger over bottom of funnel to control amount of batter released.
Turn with large fork and cook on each side. Drain on paper towels.
Sift powdered sugar over immediately.
Can use cinnamon too.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain the fruits and save their juices.
Dissolve jello in boiling water using the reserved fruit liquid to make 1 3/4 cups of liquid.
Pour into 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 package of cream cheese.
Mash it in.
When jello is set, add fruit and nuts. Chill until firm.
Combine the remaining cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over jello mixture. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill.
Delicious.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: candy apple delight
directions: Cut all fruit and the Snickers bars into small bite-size pieces.
Fold into whipped topping.
Reserve a few strawberries and pecans for garnishes, if desired.

title: baked fish
directions: Put the seasonings and bread crumbs on top of the fish.
Put a little oil on bottom of baking dish.
Place fish in baking dish. Bake about 20 minutes at 300°, then add water and baste.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients
in microwave oven.
Stir thoroughly. Stir in 1 box of Crispix or Rice Chex cereal.
Coat well.
Divide 1 pound confectioners sugar into 2 Ziploc bags.
Shake until coated.
"Puppy Chow" is crunch at first!

title: honey-walnut dressing
directions: Combine oil and mustard with a wire whisk; stir in vinegar and water.
Add honey, whisking until blended.
Add nuts; cover and chill.
Just before serving toss with torn fresh spinach, radishes, watercress and crumbled cooked bacon, if desired.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Layer jalapeno dip, guacamole dip and sour cream. Sprinkle taco
seasoning. Cut through. Do not stir, then layer tomatoes, onion and olives. Top with cheese. Chill several hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Cut both sides of steak into diamond pattern, about 1/8-inch into meat.
Place in plastic bag.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour into bag.
Press out air and fasten securely.
Refrigerate overnight, turning bag occasionally.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.
Place meat on grill over hot coals or on rack of broiler.
Grill or broil 6 minutes, turn.
Grill or broil 4 to 6 minutes or to desired doneness, brushing frequently with reserved marinade.
Remove meat to platter.
With sharp knife held at a slant, slice meat very thinly across the grain.

title: strawberry roll
directions: Mix and pour berries over mixture.
Bake at 425° (I found about 30 minutes).

title: pound cake with glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Separate eggs. Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, then set aside.
Cream butter, shortening and 2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
