Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, ending with dry ingredients, to cake mixture.
Add flavorings.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage; drain.
Press rolls into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: taco mac
directions: Prepare shells and cheese mix according to package directions. Stir in sausage, taco sauce and seasoning. Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese, if desired. Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: rice krispies date bar
directions: Take at least 2 cups Rice Krispies and put in bowl, set aside. Beat egg and add white sugar, oleo, vanilla and chopped nuts (if you want, good without also).
Beat and stir together in pan on heat.
Beat oleo first and then add other ingredients.
Heat and stir until hot and leaves the pan and thickens good.
Then pour over Krispies and mix well.
Leave cool and when you can handle, just roll into balls.
I make small ones and dip in shredded coconut.
Keeps well.

title: marble chiffon cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and cool.
Sift dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Make a well, then add in order the oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla, then beat until smooth with a spoon.
In large mixing bowl, beat very stiff peaks 1 cup egg whites (7 to 8) and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Do not underbeat.
Pour egg yolk mixture gently over whites.
Blend; do not stir.
Put 1/2 batter in a bowl; pour cocoa mixture gradually, folding until blended.
Then pour in tube pan alternating dark and light.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes in an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
When done, top springs back when touched.
Turn upside-down on neck of bottle until cold, then ice.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Beat together egg and water.
Stir into pecans and coat well. Mix with other ingredients.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: emerald salad
directions: *Put Jell-O water on stove.
Melt marshmallows; add Jell-O. Remove.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix and set in refrigerator in a mixing bowl until it starts to thicken.
Take out, stir in nuts and whipped cream.
Stir lightly.
Pour in dish you'd like for it to mold in and return to refrigerator to set.

title: pecan cake
directions: Melt bark and water.
Let stand to cool.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and white bark, then add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Fold in coconut and pecans.

title: strawberry soup
directions: In a blender or food processor, puree 4 cups of strawberries. Add apple juice and blend for 1 minute.
Pour soup into bowls. Top each serving with a dollop of yogurt.
Slice the remaining strawberries and add before serving.
Makes 14 small servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove; drain and reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until soft, but not brown.
Add potatoes, corn, celery, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend flour and remaining broth.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat and add milk.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Top with bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Put all ingredients in large bowl and beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or frost after cake is cool.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add soup, milk, salt and softened cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
In casserole dish, put layer of chicken, then torn tortillas, then sauce.
Repeat. Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cola cooler(cooking with kids)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cola.
Pour in 4 small glasses.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Top with a tablespoon of Cool Whip and maraschino cherry.

title: whip cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: jello popsickles
directions: Mix jello, kool-aid and sugar in hot water to dissolve. Add cold water. Put in containers and freeze.

title: shrimp salad
directions: With sharp knife, trim tops from onions; chop tops fine.
Wash spinach and shred.
Put in salad bowl or mound on individual salad plates.
On top of greens, pile chopped onion tops, then shrimp. Arrange onions spoke fashion around salad.
In a jar with tight fitting lid, shake soy sauce, salad oil and pepper.
Combine thoroughly.
Use as dressing for salad.

title: low-fat red beans and rice
directions: Combine ingredients; let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Put over white rice.
Delicious and quick.
Makes 2 generous helpings.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a glass bowl; sprinkle with seasonings (salt, basil, oregano and garlic powder) between each layer.
Seal the salad with mayonnaise, cover with Swiss cheese and sprinkle top with paprika.
Chill overnight.
Serve by scooping down through, not tossing.

title: quick bread
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator to rise (about 2 hours).

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up the lettuce and cauliflower.
Chop the onion.
Mix together and pat with paper towel until very dry. Cook the bacon until crisp. Crumble and layer with first ingredients.

title: conversation salad
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candies in hot water while coming to a boil. Dissolve gelatin in hot cinnamon water.
Add ice water, lemon juice and applesauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add chopped nuts.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise well.
Swirl cheese mixture in gelatin.
Turn into mold and chill.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream the cheese and eggs together.
Add 1 cup of sugar gradually until mixed together.
Add vanilla.
Lightly grease a pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Drain juice from a medium can crushed pineapple.
Mix 1 tablespoon of corn starch.
(If you prefer, you can use any kind of canned fruit topping, do not drain or add corn starch.)
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour, lemon flavor and 7-Up. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done (toothpick comes out clean).

title: black bean chili salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except olives and tortillas.
Spread on tortillas; sprinkle with olives.
Roll and wrap each tightly with Saran.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Slice into 1-inch slices.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: family casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion, stirring to separate meat particles.
Stir in soup, water, beans and noodles.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven about 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: early rising biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly.
Mix oil and milk.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Brush cooking pan with butter before putting in hot oven. Cook until brown on top and bottom.

title: banana bobs
directions: Cut bananas in fourths; insert ice cream sticks.
Freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate.
Dip bananas into mixture.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place on waxed paper-covered baking sheet.
When firm, wrap in foil.
Return to freezer.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Beat together eggs and sugar. Add mashed bananas, oil, and vanilla. In a separate bowl, sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Make a well in the dry ingredients and add the wet mixture all at once. Blend just until moistened. Stir in chocolate chips. Bake in muffin tins 18-20 minutes (12-15 minutes for mini muffins). Cool on rack.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks, at 450°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt margarine. Stir in sugar, vanilla, eggs and bananas. Chop nuts and add to mixture. Add flour and stir well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 2 loaf pans until spongy on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and debone.
Put a layer of chicken, then a layer of soup, sour cream and poppy seed, then a layer of margarine and cracker crumbs.
Repeat and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cake(serves 12)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and Pet milk in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips. Continue to stir until smooth.
Spread on cake.
Tastes like chocolate covered cherries!

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Wash and drain beans; then place in a 4 to 6-quart saucepan. Cover with water.
Add Tabasco sauce, salt, pepper and hambone. Put lid on and soak overnight.
(You can rapid boil for 1 hour instead.)
The next day (or after rapid boiling) fill pan with water.
Add onions, garlic, bay leaf and thyme.
Bring to a boil; then simmer, stirring occasionally.
After about an hour, remove hambone and bay leaf.
Continue simmering until beans are soft. Occasionally mash several beans on side of pan to form soupy mixture.
Slice sausage and add for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice with buttered French bread.

title: deep dish pizza crust
directions: In the bowl of an electric mixer, dissolve the yeast in the water.
Add the oils, cornmeal and 3 cups of flour.
Beat for 10 minutes with the mixer.
Add the dough hook and mix in the additional 2 1/2 cups flour.
Knead for several minutes with the machine (it is hard to do this by hand, since the dough is very rich and moist).

title: dante's salsa
directions: Chop or dice onions and tomatoes as fine or chunky as you would like your salsa.
Mix all ingredients.
Measurements of each are variable, of course.
The salsa will become more flavorful in its own juices.
You can always throw in more tomatoes, etc., and keep it going.
Another idea is to throw in some canned tomatoes with some of their juice.
Enjoy with your favorite nacho chips or tortilla chips.
This can be hot stuff.
Ole!!

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs; add all ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes into a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Make a dressing of remaining ingredients and stir in with potatoes.

title: cauliflower and cheese bake
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions just until tender; drain well.
Halve any large pieces.
Arrange cauliflower in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to oil mixture and mix well.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken stove top meal
directions: Cook and debone chicken, saving broth.
Fix stuffing according to package directions.
Mix in deboned, cooked chicken.
Butter large baking dish; place ingredients in dish.
Pour chicken broth over chicken and Stove Top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mammie's pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until smooth.
Cook as you would regular pancakes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti and cook in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and blanch with cold water.
Toss with remaining ingredients, except tomatoes, and marinate overnight.
Add tomatoes just before serving.
This will keep in the refrigerator up to one week.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Mix together.
Pour over pork chops.
Place in oven and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Turn after the first side is brown at 350°.

title: butternut pound cake(best i've tasted!)
directions: Hint:
Bring all ingredients to room temperature before you start.
Sift flour before measuring.

title: creamy fruit pie
directions: Roll out pastry into a 12-inch circle.
Place on 12-inch pizza pan or baking sheet.
Form 1/2-inch rim; flute edges.
Prick crust with fork.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber pickles #1
directions: Layer
vegetables; sprinkle with salt and ice.	Let set 3 hours;
wash
off.	Combine
5 cups sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard
seed
and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar and cream together.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Add flavoring and flour.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate morsels. Press into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
After cool, cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: scrumptious pecans
directions: Cook sugars and sour cream until mixture forms a medium firm ball when dropped into a cup of cold water.
Add vanilla and pour over pecans.
Blend well.
Pour onto waxed paper and cool. Separate and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a greased casserole (3 to 4-quart size), thin slice zucchini until bowl is 1/2 full.
Cook onion and pepper until soft; add hamburg and cook until meat is done.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat mixture and pour half over zucchini slices.
Add half of Mozzarella and sharp cheeses on top of sauce mixture, then start over with more thin zucchini, the sauce and cheese on top of the sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Excellent summer dish!

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix until forms a stiff dough.
Use cookie press or roll into small rolls.
Bake at 325° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf turkey
directions: Oil 1-quart loaf pan.
Mix ingredients by hand, except catsup and cheese.
Scoop mix into pan and spread catsup over.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken breast in wine
directions: Mix soups together. Add sherry and garlic. Place chicken breasts in casserole; cover with soup mixture. Sprinkle parsley and almonds on top. Cover and cook in oven 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 2 balls.
You may roll in chopped nuts or paprika.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Rub butter over bottom of a casserole dish or baking pan.
Fill half full with fresh fruit.
Pour egg mixture over fruit.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Pare and cube potatoes; boil, but do not allow them to become mushy.
Drain and set aside.
Fry the bacon and onion together. Reserve bacon fat.
In reserved fat, add flour and stir until smooth.
Add the sugar, vinegar and water; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour over potatoes, bacon, onion and celery seed.
Add salt, if desired.
Serve warm.

title: punch
directions: Mix well in punch bowl.
Float sherbet on top.

title: hot potato salad
directions: *Note:
Do not use Heinz or cider vinegar.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream until fluffy the butter and sugar.
Add and mix well the beaten eggs and vanilla.
Combine and mix well the sour cream, baking soda and sifted flour.
Add sour cream mixture and flour alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well after each addition. Add mashed bananas, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans, small size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Enjoy!

title: white chocolate key-lime pie
directions: Combine cream and white chocolate morsels in a medium sauce pan over low heat. Cook 5 minutes or until morsels melt stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add sour cream, lime rind and juice. Stir well. Pour into crust. Cover and chill at least 8 hours.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 300°.
In a bag, put confectioners sugar; coat cooked cookies with this.

title: cauliflower mushroom soup
directions: Simmer cauliflower and onion in water until very tender. Drain; save liquid.
Puree in blender in 1 1/2 cups of liquid.

title: puppy tails
directions: Mix with your hands.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add flour gradually.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Shape into small crescents and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a slow (325°) oven about 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm, then again when cold.
This works better if put in the refrigerator a while before shaping into crescents.

title: jello mold
directions: Mix 1 c hot water with cranberry gelatin mix. Add cranberry sauce. Mix all together, then add fruits like apples, oranges, grapes or nuts. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cut up bananas and with your hand, coat them with lemon juice real good.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk and stir. Add Cool Whip and stir.

title: apricot sangria blanco
directions: In a large bowl, pitcher or punch bowl combine wine, liqueur and apricot juice.
Refrigerate until chilled or overnight. Before serving, stir in sparkling water and fruits.
Serve over ice in large wine goblets, adding a few slices of fruit to each glass.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: applesauce and raisin bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan, well greased and floured, at 325° until done.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Beat margarine until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs, beat.
Add cinnamon to flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas a small amount at a time.
Turn into greased loaf pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients.
Put cherries on top and sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
In a baking pan, put in rice, salt, pepper, bouillon cubes, cut-up onion, College Inn beef broth and one can of water.
Place browned pork chops on top of liquid. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with vegetable or applesauce.
Delicious!

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream all ingredients in a bowl and spread on cooled cake.

title: lynsy's quiche(breakfast casserole)
directions: Mix together the eggs, heavy cream, cheese and onion. Pour into crust. Top with crumbled bacon. Pour into crust and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1/2 cup warm water; mix well.
Beat egg; add to yeast mixture; set aside.
In large bowl, add 1 cup water, salt, sugar and oil together.
Mix well, adding flour 1 cup at a time until mixture is bouncy and not sticky.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours in a warm place, then punch down.
Before baking, make out rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 410° for 12 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter.

title: one month frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in deep bowl; whip for 15 minutes.
Will keep up to 1 month and is delicious!

title: corned beef
directions: Combine orange, onion, celery, carrot, spices and water. Place corned beef in foil and cover with mixture.
Wrap and bake for 4 hours in 300° oven.

title: savory stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine all ingredients except 1 cup water and the flour.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 4 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove from oven.
In a covered jar, shake 1 cup water and flour until blended; stir in stew.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy fruit gelatin salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and save.
Dissolve gelatin (5 ounces) in boiling water.
Add pineapple syrup/juice.
Blend in sour cream until smooth (leave no speckles of white).
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan; refrigerate until thickened.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Put sliced potatoes in 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on potatoes.
Stir in soups.
Put slices of butter on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until potatoes are tender when pricked with a fork.

title: pasta with smoked salmon in a cream dill sauce
directions: Cook pasta in large pot of boiling water (salted) until tender, but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.

Meanwhile, melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat. Add salmon and cook until fish turns light pink, stirring frequently, about 2 minutes. Stir in cream and tomato paste. Cook until sauce is heated through, about 2 minutes. Stir in 2 teaspoons dill and cayenne pepper. Mix pasta into sauce, adding pasta cooking liquid by tablespoonfuls as needed to moisten. Divide pasta among 4 shallow bowls. Sprinkle with remaining dill and serve.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese sit out to get soft.
Mix cream cheese, 1 package of chopped corned beef, onion, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix and set in refrigerator to get firm.
Shape in ball and roll in other package of chopped corned beef.

title: blue ribbon corn relish
directions: Chop all the vegetables coarsely, then combine and boil for 40 minutes.
Seal in pint jars.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Note:
The best bet is to buy shoulder or top sirloin London broil; remove all visible fat and grind it yourself.

title: crock-pot ribs and kraut
directions: Put kraut, ribs and apple into crock-pot.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic salt on top.
Sprinkle 2 to 3 tablespoons brown sugar on top. Turn crock-pot on high.
Cook 5 to 6 hours or until meat is cooked into small pieces.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add sugar and meal; cream well, then add 1 egg at a time and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Add vinegar, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Pour in an unbaked pastry shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue cooking for 30 minutes.

title: german cheese cake
directions: Use 10-inch spring-form pan.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and 1 cup sugar in large bowl; beat 25 minutes on medium speed.
Meanwhile, combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Press onto bottom and sides of pan. Chill in freezer 15 minutes.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until top is very brown.
Turn off oven; let stay 2 hours with door ajar.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down surprise
directions: Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes at high speed. In another large bowl, combine sugar, margarine and cream cheese. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Spoon evenly over coconut and pecans within 1-inch of edges.

title: julie's ham balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form into balls.
Place into 11 x 13 jelly roll pan.
Mix and pour over balls.
Bake at 350° uncovered 1 hour 15 minutes.
Turn halfway through cooking.
Spoon juice from pan over ham balls before returning to the oven.

title: revved-up rib sauce
directions: Mix ingredient well and let stand to mellow at least a few hours.
Give sauce a good stir before using.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Stuff the green pepper with the tuna mixture and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour the 1/2 cup tomato juice over the stuffed pepper.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add cheese, soup and carrots; mix well.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole and top with stuffing.
Melt remaining margarine and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: green bean bake
directions: Mix milk, soup and pepper.
Add beans and 1/2 onion rings. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and cook 5 minutes more.

title: no bull cafe spinach lasagna
directions: Boil noodles for 6 to 8 minutes until almost tender.
Remove from boiling water and drop into a bowl of cold water.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Melt oleo and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Toss spaghetti with oleo; cover with 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of both cheeses and 1/2 of pepperoni.
Add mushrooms.
Top with the remaining ingredients, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven or until bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a bowl and keep cold.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons, mixing juice with the lemonade mix.
Add sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
You may add a little warm water if needed.
Add cold water and mix well.
Adjust to your taste if needed by adding more lemonade mix and/or sugar. Add ice cubes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pour oil in a 7 1/2 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place in oven at 400°.
While dish and oil heat, trim steak and pound 2 tablespoons of flour into each side.
Place in heated baking dish; turn to coat both sides.
Sprinkle on soup mix.
Pour tomato sauce, mixed with water, over all.
Cover tightly.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours until fork-tender.
Skim excess fat from gravy.

title: chicken marsala with basil and mushroom
directions: Place chicken between two sheets of wax paper, pound to approximately 1/4 inch thick.
In large bowl combine flour with next 3 ingredients.
Add chicken to flour mixture and toss to coat.
Heat 2 Tbsp. oil in large skillet over medium - high heat. Saute chicken 3 - 5 minutes per side or until done.
Remove from skillet.
Add mushrooms and remaining oil, if needed.
Saute 2 - 3 minutes.
Stir in wine and chicken broth, and remaining 3 ingredients.
Stir to loosen any browned particles, bring to boil. Return chicken to skillet, simmer uncovered 2 minutes.

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Combine Bisquick and pepper.
Add cheese and uncooked sausage. Mix until well blended.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 100 balls.
May be frozen.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Take off heat and add picante sauce and refried beans.

title: german chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Beat at low speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in morsels.
Spoon into a greased and floured, 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Let cool.
Sprinkle on powdered sugar.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add to tossed spinach, bacon, onions and oranges.

title: sugar 'n spice cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Add the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Lightly press your finger in the middle of each to make a small dent.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: herbal lo-cal dressing
directions: Combine garlic, chives and other seasonings with vinegar and 1 tablespoon of the oil in a blender.
Blend on low speed while adding remaining oil in a slow stream.
Quickly blend in yogurt and buttermilk.
Will keep one week in refrigerator.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Heat cherry juice to boiling.
Add Jell-O mix and set aside to cool.
Add nuts, Coke, cherries and 4 ounces cream cheese cut into small pieces.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Stir once.
Mix the rest of cheese with a little milk to make the consistency of icing. Put over Jell-O.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite size pieces. Saute onion, garlic and parsley about 3 minutes. Add broccoli and cauliflower; saute 5 more minutes.
Puree cream cheese in blender with 2 cups of water.
Add to veggies.
Add bouillon cubes and 6 to 8 cups water, depending on amount of veggies.
Add hot pepper sauce. Simmer mixture until veggies are to your liking.
Add green onions 10 minutes before done.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel, core and slice apples into wedges.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan and set aside.
Do not flour pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat one egg at a time into batter, then add all liquid ingredients in their order.
After both are blended, beat 5 minutes.
Pour part of batter into pan, then a layer of apples.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.
Pour more batter and repeat with apples.
Be sure you save a little batter to cover last layer of apples.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ham and cheese party sandwiches
directions: Saute onions in oleo, then add poppy seed and mustard.
Spread or split rolls; add ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Do not pull apart, split the whole package crossways, then bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Separate with knife when ready to serve.
Best warm.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Heat a 9 or 10-inch iron skillet in a 475° oven.
Saute apples in butter; set aside and keep warm.
In a blender, combine remaining ingredients in order given; blend well.
Remove skillet from oven, melt 2 tablespoons butter in it.
Arrange apples on bottom of skillet.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 375° and bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven and invert on serving plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into wedges to serve.

title: pasta and vegetable carbonara
directions: Cook pasta to desired doneness.
Drain.
Keep warm.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add bell pepper and broccoli to drippings.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in bacon and pasta.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes over medium heat or until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.

title: rice dressing - port arthur style
directions: Boil your gizzards and liver.
Chop it up into small parts. Cut up bell peppers, onion and celery.
Cook rice.
While rice is cooking, begin to make a brown gravy with flour and oil.
When gravy is dark brown, add your ground meat, gizzards and liver. Add a cup of water and let it simmer.
Add your rice and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: deluxe creamed onions
directions: Bring water to boil with salt.
Add onions, cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in half and half.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in carrots and cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour sauce over hot onions.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into flat dish and refrigerate until set.

title: stuffed prunes
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, mixing well. Spoon mixture into a pastry bag fitted with a large tip.
Pipe mixture into cavity of each cooled prune. Garnish with peanut halves, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 prunes.

title: icing
directions: Cream all together starting with about 1/4 cup sugar.
Add 1/4 cup water and end up with sugar.

title: sue's soup
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 1/2 hour, then add one large can Veg-All, undrained.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Do not boil it.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Season and cook chicken in enough water for 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Chop and saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Cook vermicelli in broth after removing chicken.
Add onions, peppers and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick. Add peas and mushrooms and shredded cheese.
Stir until melted. Add chicken.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs. Bake until slightly browned at 350°.

title: angel hash salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill overnight.
Next morning, chop cherries and pecans.
Add to pineapple mixture. Whip cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into pineapple mixture. Freeze.

title: apple yogurt delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add applesauce and cinnamon and pour approximately half into bowl.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Chill remaining gelatin until slightly thickened.
Blend in yogurt and spoon over gelatin in bowl.
Chill until set (about 3 hours.)

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Cream butter in mixer.
Add sugar gradually; add one egg at a time and beat after each (always break egg in saucer because if egg should be bad, it will ruin cake, very depressing!)
Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Always begin with flour and end with flour.

Add flavorings and pour into tube pan which has been greased with Crisco or vegetable oil (use paper towel). Line bottom with waxed paper, then dust with flour and shake off excess by tapping on pan over sink.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour (do not open oven door), then lower heat to 325° and bake another 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned soft gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and mix well.
Then drop in the eggs, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the sour milk.
Place in 8 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle top generously with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve large steaming squares with plenty of whipped or ice cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a well-greased baking dish. Bake 30 minutes until it is hot and bubbly around sides.

title: apple cinnamon french toast
directions: The day before, cook apples with oleo and cinnamon.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange bread on top.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Invert serving onto plate.

title: illinois corn-sausage chowder
directions: In a Dutch oven or kettle, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender; drain on paper towels.

title: spicy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done with seasoning salt, garlic and celery.
Take chicken out of broth and cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in margarine. Melt soups, Ro-tel tomatoes and Velveeta in microwave.
Mix chicken, sauteed vegetables, soup mixture and cooked spaghetti together. Put in casserole pan sprayed with Pam and cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch strips.
Dip strips in margarine.
Roll in other ingredients that have been mixed together.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake on 400° for 8 to 10 minutes unti lightly browned.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients and pour in greased muffin pans to bake in moderate oven.
Must be mixed with electric mixer.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix together, then add 1 pint vinegar.
Boil for 15 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Core, peel and slice apples in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low heat for 7 to 9 hours (or on high for 2 to 3 hours).
Also excellent served with cream, vanilla ice cream or whipped topping for desserts.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately and beat well.
Add vanilla and all other flavorings.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and dice the potatoes and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until soft.
Saute the sliced onions in the butter or margarine until tender.
When the potatoes are done, drain and add them to the onion mixture along with the corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Simmer until hot.
Enjoy!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for one hour.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube (Bundt) pan.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon and set aside.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and pepper in butter in skillet until tender.
Stir in flour; gradually add milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add cheese and cook over medium heat until cheese melts.
Combine ham and potatoes with cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine melted butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O with one cup of boiling water.
Stir in pie filling and pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex glass dish or pan. Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: pull-apart rolls
directions: Thaw dough.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cut dough in 1 x 1-inch balls.
Spread nuts in bottom of baking pan.
Dip pieces of dough into mixture then put into pan.
Press into the nuts.
Cover with foil and let dough rise in the refrigerator overnight.
Or if in a hurry, 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out at once onto a foil lined cookie sheet.

title: meat sauce
directions: Cook hamburger and drain fat.
Add onion and pepper; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandma jerry's monkey bread
directions: Snip biscuits (with kitchen scissors) into quarters.
Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
In a large bowl, coat the quartered biscuits with butter, cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Save a small amount of the butter mixture.
Into a greased Bundt pan, pour the small amount of butter mixture.
Add the coated biscuits and distribute evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let it cool a "little" before you eat it.
Grandma says, "You have to eat it with your fingers."
(That's why it's called "Monkey Bread.")

title: tolorine
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
In the last 10 minutes, add shredded cheese to top.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple.
Place in 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle flour and sugar over pineapple.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over cheese.
Pour melted margarine over crackers and bake 30 minutes.

title: wild rice and cheese casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to directions on box; drain well. Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir well until it forms a thick paste.
Begin to add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted and sauce is smooth.
Add salt. Layer rice, mushrooms and cream sauce in a greased baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.
Great with venison steaks.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Shake bag or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Layer potatoes in a shallow baking or roasting pan. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: new england cake cookies
directions: Mix together and spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
A powdered sugar icing can be spread on top.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Mix oleo, flour and chopped pecans; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown (about 15 minutes).
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and coconut. Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thick; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip; sprinkle with pecans.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Butter a big flat casserole.
Place a layer of onions on bottom; then a layer of potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Mix 1/2 can of water with 1 can of soup.
Pour over potatoes.
Place slightly browned pork chops on top.
Bake covered at 350°F for 1 1/2 hrs. Uncover the last 15 min. if not brown enough.
The amounts depend on you!

title: abbeville's hot fudge pie
directions: Melt butter, then all other ingredients.
Put in pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: *You can use part rhubarb and part strawberries (fresh or frozen).

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt chocolate bars and half of the chocolate syrup over hot water. Cream the butter with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add chocolate mixture and rest of chocolate syrup.
Add flour, buttermilk mixed with soda, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well. Bake in a large, greased and floured tube pan in a 300° oven for
1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage.
Drain excess fat.
Add Velveeta cheese (it will melt in) and spices.
Spread on cocktail rye.
Place on cookie sheets and place under low broiler until slightly browned.
Can freeze on cookie sheets and place in freezer bag for later use.

title: joseph's coat vegetable salad
directions: Add enough water to vinegar to make 1/2 cup.
Combine vinegar (with water added), mustard, flour and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: seattle salmon patties
directions: Peel number of potatoes desired; roll in flour, then roll in melted oleo, then roll in crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour into ice cream mixing container.
Add condensed milk; stir well, then continue with ice cream machine until ready to eat.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package using 1 1/2 cups cold milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill. Garnish with additional Cool Whip if desired.
Makes 2 2/3 cups or 5 servings.

title: red velvet cake i
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Beat on low speed to blend, then beat on medium speed for 4 minutes. Divide batter between 3 greased and floured round cake pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add mushroom and onion.
Saute 7 minutes or until liquid evaporates.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add chicken broth, skim milk and cream cheese. Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 Tbsp.
Parmesan cheese, sherry, salt, garlic powder, pepper and pimentos.
Set aside.

title: pickled beets and onions
directions: Cook beets 30 to 45 minutes until tender; drain.
Cool and slip off stems and skins.
Slice beets 1/4 inch thick.
Slice onions thinly and add to beets.
Heat to boiling the vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour over beets and onions and let stand at least 1 hour.
Chill before serving.

title: scallops and linguine
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons olive oil, garlic and onions in frying pan.
Saute until tender.
Spice to taste (basil, freshly ground pepper and seasoning salt).
Mix by shaking milk and cornstarch. Add to onion mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add rinsed scallops. Cook for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add wine.
Simmer.
Pour over cooked linguine.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook 1 cup rice in 3 cups water until all water is absorbed. Grease casserole; spread rice evenly on bottom.
Mix 1 can of mushroom soup and 1 can of asparagus soup (rinse cans out with a little water) and pour over rice.
Put chicken pieces over rice. Spread 1 package Lipton's onion soup over all.
Seal with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients except butter.
Turn
apple
mix
into
pastry
lined pie plate. Dot with butter and
cover with top crust.
Make slits for steam to escape; seal edges.
Bake
in
425° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until crust
is
golden
brown.
"A family favorite since childhood."

title: frozen chocolate-pecan mousse ring
directions: In small bowl, mix at medium speed egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is glossy and stiff peaks form; set aside.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt, pepper, onion and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions until tender.
Drain. Place half of meat mixture in bottom of greased casserole.
Place half noodles over meat; add 1 cup sour cream.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Spread with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot dream bars
directions: Rinse apricots; cover with water.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain. Cool and chop.
Combine butter, sugar and 1 cup of the flour and blend together until crumbly.
Pack into bottom of greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Beat eggs and beat in brown sugar gradually. Sift remaining flour with baking powder
and salt.
Stir into egg and sugar mixture.
Blend in vanilla, nuts and apricots.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: gene's chili
directions: Cook garlic in oil until golden. Crumble ground round in pieces and cook 10 minutes, breaking up so that it browns evenly. Pour off some oil and drippings into another skillet and cook onions and green peppers until tender. Add back to cooked meat. Add remaining ingredients; cover and cook over low heat 1 hour. If too dry, add more tomatoes. If too much liquid, uncover and simmer longer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with salt, pepper and onions.
Reserve 1 cup chicken broth. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Put into a greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Heat and pour over chicken. Combine stuffings and sprinkle over the soup.
Mix butter and reserved broth.
Pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherry and add lemon juice and enough water to make 1 3/4 cups of liquid.
Heat to boiling and add Jell-O.
When it starts to thicken, add olives, pecans and cherries.
Chill.

title: autumn grains
directions: Combine broth and orange juice in a large sauce pan;
bring to a boil.
Add squash and next 8 ingredients (onion to ginger). Cover;
reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add raisins and barley.
Cover and cook 35 to 40 minutes or until grains are tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in pecans, serve immediately. Yield: 5 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut edges of bread and soak in milk until soft.
With fork, crumble bread into milk.
Melt butter.
Preheat oven at 375°. Butter a glass mold, 9 x 13-inch.
To bread soaked in milk, add sugar, salt, vanilla and melted butter.
Break eggs and beat slightly, adding same into vanilla mixture.
Stir together and pour into glass mold.
Place in oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be served cold in slices.

title: cheese stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In medium saucepan, cook mushrooms with butter until tender. Remove from heat.
Add cheese, parsley and bread crumbs.
Stir gently; set aside.
Bone and halve chicken.
Stuff about 1/3 of cheese mixture between skin of meat.
Place skin up in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: date squares
directions: Cook dates with sugar, orange juice and red wine.
Cook until softened.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, rolled oats, butter, walnuts, coconut, salt, baking soda and vanilla pie mix.
Press 1/2 mixture in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour date mixture on top.
Cover with remaining flour mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned, 400°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough flour to make a pancake-like batter.
Heat cooking oil in pan.
When hot, drop batter by spoonfuls into pan and fry like pancakes.
Serve hot.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer coconut and pecans in pan.
Pour prepared cake batter over nuts.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust in Pyrex dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs lightly on top.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make custard of egg, milk, juice of lemon, dry mustard and pinch of salt.
Scald the milk; stir in beaten eggs, mustard and salt.
Add lemon juice last.
When cool, pour over fruit, almonds and marshmallows; then fold in the whipped cream.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: sunflower seed waffles
directions: Blend until
smooth.
Bake in prepared waffle iron 8 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and flour.
Stir in boiling water and cook (medium) until thickened, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks slightly and stir a little of the hot mixture into them. Then add egg yolks to hot mixture with rind, salt, lemon juice and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until filling is clear, yellow and thick.
Cool slightly and fill baked pie shell.

title: date roll
directions: Mix well.
Divide in half.
Make 2 rolls.
Place on wax paper that you have sprinkled powdered sugar on.
Wrap rolls in this paper and refrigerate.
Slice to serve.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butter and blend with sugar.
Add egg and beat vigorously.
Sift flour; measure and add baking powder and salt. Sift again.
Add dry ingredients to egg and sugar mixture and mix together well.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spread dough in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares or bars while warm.
Makes 18 to 20 squares.

title: duck or pheasant salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but water cress and endive, refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
Arrange on bed of water cress and endive mixture.
Serves 4.

title: hands down cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill, then roll out.
Cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 250°.

title: chilled cream of asparagus soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except chives in food processor or blender and mix until smooth.
Chill thoroughly.
Sprinkle with chives just before serving.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour bottoms of 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round cake pans. In medium bowl, stir flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla, scraping bowl occasionally, three minutes or until smooth and creamy.
Reduce speed to low.
Beat in mayonnaise until blended.
Add flour mixture in 4 additions alternately with water.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Fill and frost as desired.
Makes one (1) 9-inch high layer cake.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix all together and dip shrimp for deep frying.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake mix.
Mix together Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping.
Punch holes in cake.
Let milk topping soak in.
Let cool.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Top with Cool Whip. Crumble up Heath bars on top of Cool Whip.

title: squash dressing
directions: Drain squash and mash.
Add all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1-quart dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and drain.
Put all other ingredients in saucepan.
Mix to blend.
Heat to boiling.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and boil for 5 minutes.
Leave covered until cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy!

title: bacon and cheese corn bread
directions: Heat cornmeal and milk over medium heat until thick and dry, stirring frequently for about 3 minutes.
Spoon cornmeal mixture into a bowl.
Add the remaining milk, butter and eggs and beat until smooth.
Stir in salt and baking powder (eliminate if you use a yellow corn bread mix).
Add red chilies, if used.
Stir in cheese and bacon and pour into a casserole dish or cake pan.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over sugar, shortening and salt in mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water; add beaten egg and mix well; add to milk mixture.
Add about 1/2 the flour; beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour; mix well.
Grease top of dough slightly and cover bowl with waxed paper and a towel. About 2 hours before baking, shape 3 small balls of dough for each greased muffin pan to make cloverleaf rolls.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Makes 1 1/2 dozen medium rolls.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Combine sugar, oil, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until well combined.
Cover and chill until dough can be handled.
Using 1 tablespoon dough, shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are firm and slightly browned.
Don't overcook! Remove and dip tops in powdered sugar again.
Cool on wire rack.

title: great smokey mountain spoon bread
directions: Mix meal, water and salt.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring.
Add milk, well beaten eggs and fat.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased, hot, cast-iron skillet to make a pone or whatever kind of dish you want.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.
Serve from container.

title: whiskey sauce
directions: Heat whiskey and sugar in small saucepan.
Add water, juice and cornstarch to large cup and blend.
Stir into whiskey mix. Add spice; stir.
Cook on low, stirring frequently, until slightly thick and dark in color, 10 to 20 minutes.
Pour over hot pudding.

title: beef and cheese pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Pour off excess liquid.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Line pie plate with crescent rolls.
Unroll and press in pan.
Beat egg and grated cheese and spread over pie shell.
Add meat mixture.
Spread 1 cup of cheese on top of meat.
Add a dash of paprika on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup and mold in greased loaf pan.
Invert on shallow 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan. Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Score top of loaf diagonally with knife handle; fill lines with catsup.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: poppy seed loaf cake
directions: Mix well with electric beater.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bubble soap
directions: Mix Dawn with water and glycerin in a dishpan.
Make bubble blowers from a straw, a kitchen funnel or a thin wire shaped in creative forms.
For spectacular bubbles, thread a string through straws to form a circle, dip in bubble solution and wave out a large bubble.

title: dip
directions: Mix sour cream, allspice and sugar.
Please dip strawberries.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Put mixture of first 6 ingredients on 3 split hamburger buns that have been placed on a baking pan.
Top each tuna puff with a slice of tomato.
Mix Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture on tomato slices.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add dissolved yeast; add buttermilk.
Knead.
Break off pieces and roll into biscuits.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: legumes fromage(cheese green beans)
directions: Heat green beans until boiling, drain and set aside.
Brown onion and mushrooms in margarine in heavy skillet.
In a medium saucepan, add and heat together flour, milk, cheese, Tabasco, soy sauce, Accent and pepper until cheese melts.
In large ovenproof baking dish, mix green beans, cheese sauce, mushrooms and onions. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and picante sauce.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch or smaller pan or casserole dish.
Layer on top:
peppers, tomatoes, olives, onion and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Doritos.

title: oyster stew
directions: Carefully clean fresh oysters or drain canned oysters.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add drained oysters and cook for 3 minutes or until edges curl.
Add milk, salt and pepper and bring almost to boiling point.
Serve hot.
Garnish with paprika. Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: rice and chicken
directions: This can be made in a crock-pot or in a baking dish in the oven.
Bake 3 hours in 350° oven or 4 hours in crock-pot on high or until tender.
Great for Sunday Dinner.

title: cabbage soup (diet)
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
To substitute for one can of condensed soup, combine 1/3 cup dry soup mix with 1 1/4 cups of cold water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add to casseroles as you would the canned product.
Makes equivalent of 9 cans of soup.
Calories 131, fat 1 g, sodium 728 mg and fiber trace.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and mustard.
Add eggs, vinegar, then boiling water.
Add butter after mixture boils.
Stir constantly over high heat until the mixture boils several minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine cake mix (less 1 cup) with 1 egg and melted margarine.
Press mixture down in 9x13x2 inch pan (grease bottom only).
Combine pumpkin pie mix with 2 eggs and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over crust.

title: food for the gods
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing until smooth.
Fold in flour, then beat again.
Add vanilla.
Fold in walnuts and chopped dates until smooth.
Pour in greased pan; spread evenly.
Lastly, sprinkle/spread a little brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: country apple pie
directions: In large bowl, stir flour into melted oleo.
Add vanilla and allspice, then stir until well mixed.
Add sugar, then apples. Stir apples until coated with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust, then top with second crust or lattice strips. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: english pea and pasta salad
directions: Combine macaroni, peas, pimento, cheese and onion in bowl; mix well. Add mayonnaise and toss to mix. Chill for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt ice cream until mixable.
Add milk and pudding.
Grind the 1 1/2 sleeves of crackers.
Place 3/4 of the crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the ice cream mixture over the crackers and place the rest of the crackers on the top.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.
Keep frozen.
Makes 20 servings.

title: bridgette's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; let cool and debone.
In a saucepan, add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth.
Bring to a boil; add seasoning packet.
In a casserole dish,
line bottom of pan with chicken and stuffing bread crumbs. Add boiling mixture and stir well.
Mix it up really good.
Top with shredded cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick mini pizzas
directions: Split muffins. Spread each half with pizza sauce.
Top with meat. Sprinkle with cheese and seasoning.
Bake in oven preheated to 400° until cheese melts and muffin is crisp.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar then sour cream; add cool whip and chocolate chips.
Chill a few hours.

title: ranch beans
directions: Dice onions and cook with bacon until browned.
Drain off grease.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Blend well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Melt brown sugar and margarine in saucepan.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool about 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and gradually add confectioners sugar until frosting is of right consistency to spread.

title: german lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces in a long Pyrex dish. Layer onion, peas and crumbled bacon.
Spread salad dressing over the top (do not toss).
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: ranchero beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, salt and pepper together.
Drain. Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Add to bean mixture.
Combine both beans, brown sugar and ketchup. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in a crock-pot for up to 8 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut into thin strips.
Spray Pam in Dutch oven and put over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steak, mushrooms and onion.
Saute 10 minutes until steak is brown and vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat and drain well.
Melt margarine in pan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add water and bouillon.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Combine yogurt and next 4 ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture and steak mixture to skillet. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring.
Do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute onions in butter in large skillet over medium heat until tender.
Cool.
Combine eggs, sour cream, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Add to onions.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and continue baking 10 to 15 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: easy nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly. Add chopped walnuts and raisins.
Pour into buttered loaf pan. Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
May use 4 gift size loaf pans.
Baking time would be approximately 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and condensed milk.
Put on low heat and bring to a boil.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes. Add the marshmallows and stir until dissolved. Add the butter. Stir until dissolved.
Add the salt.
Take off the stove and add the chocolate chips. Stir until smooth.
Add nuts, if desired.
Let set until ready to cut.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cook squash and 1/2 teaspoon salt in boiling water to cover in 2-quart saucepan for 10 minutes. Drain and cool. Cut squash in half lengthwise. Scoop out pulp and reserve, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells. Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat; add carrot, bell pepper and onion and saute until crisp-tender. Add garlic, salt, pepper and soy sauce; cook, stirring often, until vegetables are tender. Stir in reserved pulp. Spoon into shells and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, peppers and onions. Mix vinegar, sugar, spices and teaspoon of salt. Mix all together; bring to boil for 30 minutes. Put in clean jars while still hot.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, then cook spaghetti in the chicken broth.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in oleo, then melt Velveeta in this mixture.
Add soups and Ro-Tel.
Combine with chicken and spaghetti.
Season to taste.
Place in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up the cabbage.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch dish. Brown the hamburger and onion in skillet. Pour over cabbage.
Pour the rice over top.
Mix the soup with water and pour on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 300°.
Put on cheese and let melt.

title: elephant stew
directions: Saw elephant into bite-sized pieces.
Saute pieces in oil until a lovely golden brown.
In a large, clean garbage can or wheelbarrow, combine water, vegetables and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add meat.
Cover (if no cover is available, use heavy foil).
Simmer 5 days.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple syrup and water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold carrots, pineapple and nuts into slightly thickened gelatin.
Turn into individual molds or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with mayonnaise.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: To make crust, melt butter with unsweetened chocolate.
Mix in sugar and flour and form dough.
Pat
evenly into a 9-inch square baking pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: dutch oven pork chops
directions: Cook chops over medium heat until brown on both sides.
Remove chops to platter.
Cook potatoes, carrots and onions until lightly brown, adding oil if necessary.
Arrange the vegetables over and around the pork chops.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid and remaining ingredients, except peas.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low and cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes.
Add frozen peas.
Heat through.

title: baptist pie
directions: Put oranges and pineapple into blender for just a few seconds. Then, empty into a bowl and add milk and lemon juice.
Mix well and then fold in Cool Whip.
Put mixture into crusts and garnish with pecans.
Chill for 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cupcakes
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fill greased cupcake pans half full.
Bake in moderate oven.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting or plain, if desired.

title: apple butter in oven
directions: Put in roaster pan mixing all ingredients well.
Set oven at 300 degrees.
Cook for 3 to 6 hours or until thick.
Stir every 45 minutes or more.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Add tomato sauce and taco sauce. After boiling macaroni, add to mixture. While still hot, mix in cheese and serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Note:
No directions were given - just a list of ingredients. Don't try 5 cents of coconut.

title: vegetable patties
directions: Mix together and shape into flat patties or cone shape.
Drop into deep fat (hot) until brown and top with cream of celery soup or cream sauce.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, turning once.

title: salmon salad loaf
directions: Combine olives, salmon, carrot, celery, relish, lemon juice, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve over hot water.
Blend cottage cheese with mayonnaise.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Combine with olive-vegetable mixture and blend well.
Pour into mold and chill.
Unmold onto platter and garnish with salad greens.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Slowly melt together the chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from fire and add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mini marshmallows. Stir well to coat.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on 3 pieces of waxed paper.
Spoon chocolate mixture into the powdered sugar and form in 3 rolls.
Sprinkle more powdered sugar on top.
Refrigerate until firm (several hours or overnight).
Slice to serve.

title: bread
directions: Mix well to form ball.
Place in loaf pan.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Brush with butter, cook 10 minutes more.
Cool.
Slice and enjoy.

title: spring creek cafe's sweet potato pie
directions: Process sweet potato meat in blender.
Combine, in the following order:
eggs, sweet potato meat, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, nutmeg, allspice and undiluted evaporated milk. Pour into pie crusts.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce baking temperature to 350°; bake an additional 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until sharp knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool.
Garnish with whipped topping; sprinkle with ground nutmeg. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: vegetable-cheese squares
directions: For crust, unroll the crescent rolls and gently pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: quick new england baked beans
directions: In a skillet, saute bacon and onion until onion is tender; remove from heat.
Stir in honey, mustard, salt and cayenne.
Mix together with beans in a 2-quart covered baking dish.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, or until honey mixture is absorbed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine water,	beer
and oil in saucepan; heat to 120° to 130°.
Set	aside.	Combine
2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add beer mixture; beat 5 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Stir enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: barbecue deer meat
directions: Pour salt water off deer and boil meat or pressure cook in water with chopped onions, garlic powder, red pepper, salt and black pepper.
Cook until tender.
Take meat out of broth and save some broth.
Take meat off bones and chop fine.
Don't grind.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine soup, chiles, olives, sour cream, some green onion tops and onion with half of the two grated cheeses.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of mixture.
Add diced chicken to remaining mixture and roll in flour tortillas.
About 1 1/2 tablespoons to each tortilla. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add remaining mixture over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese and green onion tops. Refrigerate overnight covered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except eggs) until blended.
Add eggs, mix, then pour into graham cracker crust pie shell.
Bake at 350°. Done when knife inserted comes out clean.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: new years dinner(mexican)
directions: Cook black-eyed peas until done.
Season to taste.
Brown ground beef and smokies.
Then put ground meat, smokies and black-eyed peas in a crock-pot, on low setting.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk, salt, black pepper and red pepper.
Stir until well heated and thickened.
Add crabmeat and cream.
Heat well, then add sherry.
Delicious!

title: carrot-turnip blend
directions: Boil vegetables together with salt and sugar until soft. Drain well.
Then simmer in butter to your liking.

title: (aunt stormy's) spaghetti
directions: Using a large pot, put in tomatoes and catsup (rinse catsup bottle with water).
Add tomato paste (rinse can with water) and clove of garlic (cut up real fine).
Let that simmer while you brown ground chuck in skillet.
Add to large pot.
Brown onion and peppers in butter and add to pot.
Let it simmer from two to four hours gently.
If it gets too thick, add a little water.
If you like, add mushrooms to the sauce.
I also like to sprinkle a little oregano in sauce while it simmers.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts for approximately 20 minutes.
Break up cooked chicken and set aside.
Layer the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with frozen broccoli, chicken pieces and red pepper. Mix cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise and spread on top of other ingredients.
Sprinkle grated cheese next and bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve over rice pilaf.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat. Add all dry ingredients and beat extra well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or when it pulls away from pan.
Use a greased and floured pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Place half the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole; cover with half the onion and half the sauce; repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour, uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak the bread in the milk until it is very soft, then mash it fine.
Heat together until nearly boiling.
Beat the eggs until light and add to them the sugar, salt and vanilla.
When well mixed, stir this into the bread and milk.
Pour the whole into a baking dish; set in pan of water and bake in a slow oven (250° to 350°).
Bake until knife comes out dry, but not clean.
Top will be brown and crusty looking.

title: veggie squares
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Press out flat on cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and buttermilk dressing.
Cut up broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, green onion and tomatoes.
Mix about 1/2 of the veggies in the cream cheese mixture and spread on the crescent rolls.
Top with remaining veggies.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: beautiful fluffy white frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine egg whites, sugar, corn syrup, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes, or until stiff peaks form.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Beat again.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 1 package dried beef and other ingredients.
Shape into ball.
After chilled, top with remaining dried beef.

title: fancy garlic bread
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and garlic salt. Spread on bread that has been sliced through lengthwise.
Sprinkle with green onion and top with shredded cheese.
Broil until bubbly. Watch carefully; will burn easily. Delicious with Italian dishes or a salad. Reheat in foil.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add 3 1/2 quarts milk. Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly to avoid sticking.
Take off heat; add Carnation milk and vanilla for a 6-quart freezer.

title: tomato-onion-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In 1 inch of boiling water, cook onions, covered, for 10 minutes.
Drain.
In casserole dish, layer in order half
of the tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Sprinkle with half of salt, pepper and basil.
Repeat until all are used.
Toss crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tootsie's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and roll into balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax over water.
Dip each ball.
I use part white chocolate to give a milk chocolate coating on balls.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion together and drain.
Mix together ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar and add to meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, heat thoroughly.
Can be prepared in electric skillet, crock-pot or baked after mixing all ingredients together, but not necessary to bake.

title: nut cake
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Roll into marble size balls.
Put in freezer until almost frozen.
Melt chocolate chips in paraffin.
Dip each ball.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese together; add flour and cereal.
Shape into cookies and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Shape them into desired shape; they do not change size.)

title: carob fudge
directions: Boil carob in water, stirring for 5 minutes until smooth paste.
Mix all ingredients and press into a square pan and refrigerate.

title: raspberry-banana frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and cover.
Process until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and butter.
Put half of it in the bottom of casserole.
Cook zucchini, carrots and onions for 10 minutes.
Add the sour cream and chicken soup.
Put this mixture on top of stuffing and then the rest of the stuffing on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until boils and thickens.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Cool.
Add fresh peaches to which Fruit Fresh has been added.
Stir gently and pour into baked pie crust.
Chill overnight.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: sour cream-zucchini casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion; season with salt and pepper. When hamburger mixture is cool, prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Combine hamburger, sour cream, soup, carrots and zucchini.
Spread half of meat mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer half of the stuffing over meat, then the rest of hamburger mix and top with the remaining stuffing.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: "talk of the town" rice pudding cake
directions: Wash rice and put in a 4-quart pan.
Add just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil and drain.
Add milk and cook rice until done.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add these to the warm rice with rind and raisins; blend well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a well buttered 10-inch angel food tube pan, which has been dusted with cracker crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
Loosen with knife.
Invert; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix & spoon into cupcake pans 2/3 full. Beat sugar & cheese until smooth. Beat egg & salt until light.
Put cheese mixture with egg. Add chocolate chips and drop by teaspoonsful on top of cupcakes. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. May frost when cool but not necessary.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of vanilla wafers on bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add a layer of banana slices and of pudding.
Continue layering wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites with salt until foamy throughout. Gradually beat in sugar and continue beating until mixture will form stiff shining peaks.
Spoon lightly onto pudding, sealing edges well.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 stick melted margarine and crushed cornflakes.
Put in large 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with cornflakes and rest of margarine.
Bake for at least 45 minutes in 350°
oven.
Makes large casserole.

title: pineapple upside-down
directions: Melt butter in pan; spread brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and nuts.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar.
Add pineapple juice and flour mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour over pineapple. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: polynesian beets
directions: *One tablespoon cornstarch for thickening equals 2 tablespoons flour.

title: joy's corned beef and noodles casserole
directions: Stir and combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
